author: @Victoriaa505
text: This is one of my favorite songs. With this song, "Stray Kids" showed their high level of vocals. This song is simply beautiful and forces you to sit in silence and listen to feel and admire. (I won't comment on the rap side because I don't feel the need, the vocals are not what counts in this song) vocally, everyone is amazing, everyone delights in the same way at a given moment, but I wanted to highlight Lee Know - he is very underrated, he gets very little lyrics and very he rarely gets a chance to show his skills. He has a truly beautiful voice, in this song I wanted to fall on my knees with him because he allowed me to hear him clearly and passionately.

author: @leslielopez8096
text: This song reminds me of a really dark moment in my life. I took a pill about 5 years ago that was prescribed by a doctor. I had trouble sleeping and the days that followed were miserable. Then one day bam, I had trouble processing the world around me. Everything inside my head hurt and I was in mental torture. I spent a whole week like that. I got out of it but the effects really freaked me out bc of how strong they were. During that whole week I felt so much pain. This song really captures what that week meant to me.

text: Voices is one of the best performance videos of stray kids. The location, filming everything is aesthetic. author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Bang Chan. As Iâ€™ve frequently noted, I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade but I have never seen somebody like you in the musical field before. What you have been and are capable of, is absolutely untouchable and Iâ€™ve learned that there is nothing that can take the sincerity and passion out of your character. I will say, despite being a long-time fan of K-Pop, I didnâ€™t become a Stay until the just a few years ago. I donâ€™t know how I went so long without knowing or supporting Stray Kids sooner, but I am completely and utterly thrilled to be a Stay now. To this day I wouldnâ€™t know about Stray Kids if it werenâ€™t for the Stay. I heard so much conversation among the fans of Stray Kids about how fearless of a leader you were, and I became curious. Over the course of those few years, I have spent my free time, which I lately have a lot of, getting to know you and your members. It started with liking a few songs, but then Stay, who talk with so much praise about you and your members, convinced me to see what was lying beneath the meaning of your music. I began to watch Stray Kids content whenever and of whatever I could, and I gradually fell more in love with your performance and personality overall. I have come to know how passionate and dedicated you are and have always been to music and performing. Even before Stray Kids was officially formed and debuted, you had music in your heart and I can see that clearly every time that you go on stage with your members. Not only do you have a naturally beautiful voice evident of vocal capability and strength, but your dancing skills are rigid and flawless beyond words. Your presence on stage is nothing less than inspirational and you ground and center your members in a way that Iâ€™ve never seen before. You always bring everyone together and emit unity on and off the stage. Outside of your musical performances, however, I have gotten the pleasure of getting to know you and your personality. I donâ€™t even really know where to start by how touched I am at the positive impact you have already made on this world despite still having so much more left to say. Before I became a Stay, I didnâ€™t know much about what Stray Kids had gone through to get where they are now; and I didnâ€™t know just how much you went through either. However, the loving Stay introduced me to how hard you worked individually to keep your membersâ€™ heads above water through the rigorous days of training, performing, and other events that swarmed you. I was, and still am absolutely mesmerized at what you have accomplished to make this group possible, and successful beyond its comprehension. Thanks to the Stay, I know that before Stray Kids even debuted, you formed an unbreakable and unique bond with each of the members as well as one together as a whole. You lift your members up with the emotional and motivational weight of all the words that youâ€™ve ever said to them. To know that there would be no Stray Kids without you makes me love you in a manner that is simply indescribable. I know that I, your members, and the Stay have so much respect and admiration for you because of everything that youâ€™ve done and overcome in just the beginning of your musical journey. I have gotten the honor of seeing at least some of the groupâ€™s history and how it came to be, and seeing how you were a huge part of that makes me appreciate having you in my life more than I did before. You have single-handedly helped carry this group to victory and done so much to ensure that you stay together. You have always kept your promise that you, in words that I once heard you say, â€œDonâ€™t leave anybody behind.â€ On top of leading your group to all of its success and glory, your are also humble and kind and always put them first. You sacrifice so much for your music, your members, and Stay and we recognize how hard you work day in and day out. You are so funny, clever, and know not to take life too seriously. At the same time you are professional, intelligent, respectful, and wise beyond your years. You are every bit qualified to be the leader that you are and I hope you never doubt your capability of doing that because Stay have seen you build something beautiful with your own two hands from the ground up. You never gave up even when the world encouraged you to and from that I find so much inspiration that I donâ€™t even know how how to thank you. All I do know is that your family and parents are the most proud of you and love you more than any of us do. I canâ€™t even imagine how strong they think you are for what youâ€™ve created. I donâ€™t want to put any more pressure or a burden on you, but so much would crash and burn without you and I hope that our love and support is enough to lift you up through your darkest times. You deserve so many blessings and praise. I just hope that you know your efforts are being recognized every second and that Stay, your members, and your family love you beyond words. I canâ€™t thank you enough for everything that youâ€™ve already done. You make Stay and your members feel so valued and desired and I know that only you can do that. I canâ€™t wait to see what you do next because I know that I couldnâ€™t leave you or stop supporting you if I tried. On behalf of your friends, Stay, members, and most importantly family, I pray that this birthday is filled with all of those blessings that you deserve and that itâ€™s everything that you desire. I pray that you and your loved ones remain in good good health and good faith, because the world is relying on it in order to fully heal and love each other. Happy birthday Bang Chan, and from the bottom of my heart, we absolutely adore you. You make Stray Kids all around the world stay.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Felix. You have to be one of the biggest blessings on this Earth. I know that I crossed paths with Stray Kids for a reason, and I know you were one of those reasons. Before I even knew anything about Stray Kids, I knew about you. Three years ago, when I got my introduction to K-Pop and was beginning to like quite a few groups, I didnâ€™t know much about Stray Kids, but I did know about you. I couldnâ€™t go anywhere without hearing anybody talk about you, and that was what lead me into wanting to find out more about you, and your position in Stray Kids. I came into the fandom blindly, without knowing any of the names of the members, and relied on the Stay to tell me everything I needed to know about you. It was because of the intense loving fanbase that you have that I learned, in only a matter of days, what a rare talent you are. The depth of your voice combined with your passionate vocals is one of the most beautiful sounds I have ever heard. Your rapping and singing abilities are entirely specific to you and are so captivatingly intriguing, that I knew I loved you from the moment I first got introduced to you. You are so flexible with your voice and on the stage; and once I first got notice of how outstanding you are, I couldnâ€™t stop discovering what made you so enticing and lovable. You are so recognized and appreciated for your natural talent that word reached me about how special you are before I even got a chance to know who Stray Kids really were. Since then, I have been a Stay, and I can say that you are an individual that led me to become one. I have never seen someone with such a bright presence and spirit completely dominant on stage and create an environment so mysterious and energetic for so many people. You bring to music what nobody else can, and I am so happy you share that with all of your Stay when you could be doing something else. I see how happy that you make your members, and since I am a relatively new fan, I still have yet to learn everything that Stray Kids has been through in the years that youâ€™ve been active. However, I have already seen how much you have healed your members when they needed you the most and provided for Stay a support system that they can actually believe in. You are such a delight to be around and I get so happy just seeing your face these days, especially with all of the craziness thatâ€™s in the world. You have a strong-willed heart, and you are extremely kind, forgiving, and non-judgmental. I have loved becoming so acquainted with you and appreciating all of your hard work because you deserve it! You do so much for everyone, and I hope you know that you are so loved and Stay are so grateful to you for even the little things that you do every single day! Never give up and I hope you continue to be the person that uplifts Stay and your members! I know that no matter what happens, Stay will always support you and I canâ€™t tell you how much you really mean to all of us. Thank you so much for being such a kind and loving human being, and for accepting me and so many people into your family as Stay! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future. On behalf of your friends, members, Stay, and most importantly, your family, I want to wish you the most entertaining and enjoyable birthday ever! Felix, have fun, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, stay safe, Happy, Birthday, and WE LOVE YOU!!!!!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Jisung. Deciding to support Stray Kids has been one of the best decisions of my entire life, and you are one of the people who are the reason why I do so. I only just started supporting K-Pop groups three years ago, and I discovered so many groups because I had the time on my hands. However, since I graduated high school I have found I have been a lot busier and unfortunately havenâ€™t been able to dedicate my time to supporting these groups that I like. I didnâ€™t think that there was going to be any time left for me to support another group, but then you came along. My first experience from Stray Kids was the song â€˜Side Effects,â€™ and it fortunately was a song where I got to hear the vocal and rap blend of your versatile voice. Next, it was â€˜Boxer,â€™ which despite it being an upbeat song, almost moved to to tears because of how beautiful your voice sounded.  After that, I watched you on â€˜The Masked Singer,â€™ and I couldnâ€™t stop from there. I quickly learned that there is nothing that you canâ€™t do. You are a stunning vocalist, flexible rapper, and outstanding dancer. Overall, this allows for you to be one of the most exceptional performers that I, and other Stay, have ever come to know. I knew, right from the moment that I heard your voice, that I had to have more. I kept going, and since then, I have come to learn so much about you and the legacy that you have already left on music. Stay is one of the most unique fandoms that I have been so fortunate to join, and I now know that you are one of the reasons why. I had always thought about Stray Kids as being such an active group and constantly releasing music and content to show how much Stay meant to them, only to find out that you have been such a huge part of that all along. I havenâ€™t even been a Stay for very long yet, but I already have seen the indescribable impact that you left on Stay. It is unlike anything that I have ever seen. I can see how happy, inspired, and desperate that Stay are to reciprocate every ounce of love that you give to them. When I became aware of this, I knew I had to be a part of it. You are so generous, honest, loyal, and possibly most importantly, I have seen you completely change the type of day someone is having just by setting the mood. Whether it be your members, or Stay, you always make sure that everyone is having the best day possible, even it means you have to sacrifice your mood for somebody else. Because you are just naturally funny and inclined to make everybody around you happy, you have an outlook on life that causes everybody you ever meet to be better and happier because of it all. As Iâ€™ve said, I havenâ€™t been a Stay for long at all, but on behalf of the other fans, I already canâ€™t even thank you enough for everything that you do every day. You have such a refreshing personality that we all need, especially at this time in the world. I hope that you never lose the innate kindness in your heart and actions; and I am so blessed to be able to thank you for all of it today. On behalf of Stay, who encouraged me to join them and showed me that there are no limits to your love, your members, who adore you quite possibly in a way that no other person can, and your friends and family, who we know are so proud of you, I want to wish you the happiest birthday ever Jisung! I pray that you and your l loved ones stay safe and find happiness and worth in the future. I am so proud of everything that you have accomplished and am so glad I get to see you grow each day now! PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE stay safe, and I hope you know how much we all absolutely love you so much!!! Be happy!!!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Seungmin, I would like to wish you an early happy birthday, as the time is drawing close. My introduction to Stray Kids was unique in that the reason I decided to support it was because of the fans. I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade, and I have come to support many groups. However, becoming a Stay was a new experience for me because it was the first time that I joined a group because the love from the fans was so strong, I knew I needed to be a part of it. I learned about each Stray Kids member one at a time, and what I learned and admired very quickly about you was your individuality. Every member stands out for their own reasons, but your charm is retaining your individuality and independence while still being a part of something bigger. I became an official Stay two years ago, and since then I have gotten to see how well you blend in with your members. You are such a valued member of Stray Kids, that we canâ€™t see them existing without you. Youâ€™ve also created a journey of personal growth and development both musically and personally and I have felt so connected to you since Iâ€™ve become a Stay. Your personality is so enticing in that sometimes you can be quiet and shy, but other times you are very vocal and humorous with your members. Itâ€™s very powerful that you can be so sweet and naturally kind-hearted without saying any words sometimes, while other times, being open and direct about how you feel. I can see how much your loving personality has impacted your members, because Iâ€™ve never seen them happier than when you spend time with them. You are always making your members laugh and motivating them just by putting one smile on their face. I feel so inspired watching you build such a trustworthy relationship with them and want to be at least half as generous as you. I know that your members are so thankful for you everyday and couldnâ€™t be anywhere near as successful without you. I have never heard a fanbase talk so highly and frequently of a member in the way that they honor you. I always hear Stay talking about how gentle and sweet you are; and how much positivity and love you bring to the world wherever you go. Stay talk about your rare, emotion-based, and versatile voice that captivates everyone into your performance. They talk about the flawless and effortless dancing that you work so hard to share with us and spoil us with on every stage. They talk about your overall professional and inspirational performance on stage that leaves every Stay wanting to spend more time with you. Iâ€™ve heard so much about how beloved you are Seungmin, and once I became a Stay, I am seeing for myself how much you are adored all over the world. Not only by Stay, but the loving influence that you have on your members makes them and everyone that you meet a kinder and more loving person. Stay praise and speak so highly of you, that I canâ€™t say Iâ€™ve experienced a family this loving toward an idol. I just want you know how much love there is everywhere all around the world for you. You are the reason that so many people lift their heads up and keep going another day, including me. There is so much negativity going on in the world right now, and to have you as a role model and see it not preventing you from sharing more love is making the world even stronger and closer to restoring to its greatness. I really feel like we donâ€™t deserve you sometimes because your genuine strong heart is hard to come across these days. I hope that we can repay you even a little bit of the love youâ€™ve shown us in just a few years since your debut. I know you have worked so hard to be where you are and I donâ€™t even want to pretend to know how much youâ€™ve probably gone through. I just want to take this day, and every day afterwards to recognize and let you become aware of how much I, Stay, and your members really love you. I know that your parents and the rest of your family are prouder of you than any other person and they respond to every action you take with great respect, understanding, and love. Your members and family are so lucky to have you and I know that are thankful and appreciative of you every day. Thank you so much for sacrificing more than we know just to make us happy even a little bit. On behalf of your friends, members, Stay, and loving family, I hope that the love that you have given to this world is given back to you on this special day and every day in your future. Please surround yourself by the people that love you most, and let the love that we have for you give you the most fulfillment! I wish you nothing but happiness for you and your loved ones, and I pray that you all stay safe. Happy birthday Seungmin! We adore you so much and we are so grateful to have such a bright light in our lives.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Changbin. It only took a few months for me to fall completely in love with Stray Kids and you, even when I barely knew anything about the group. What caught my attention right away was your rapping skills. I've never heard anybody rap like you, and I know I won't for the rest of my life. There's something about the way you do it, and I guess some people really are born with talents. I am so glad you are sharing your musical ability with the world because you were meant to do it. The charisma, passion, and ease into which you weave into your rap enticed me from the moment I first heard a Stray Kids song and it was history from there. It was impossible to not become a STAY, and it's one of the best decisions I've made in my life. I hope that you keep rapping and singing and that you flourish and grown in Stray Kids, as well as individually, as long as you live. I am so grateful I stumbled upon your once-in-a-lifetime voice, and am so blessed to get to hear it whenever I want. Please do not stop making music because I, and every other STAY, need your voice to keep going another day. I am so proud of everything you've accomplished in just two years in SKZ and can't wait to see what you do next. I will always support you and look forward to hearing what else you can do with your versatile voice and outstanding performance etiquette. Keep dancing perfectly, singing beautifully (as you demonstrate in this video), and most of all, rapping, which is what you do best unlike no other. You are an absolutely beautiful rapper, and I hope you never give that up for anyone or anything. I absolutely adore you, and thank you for working so hard every day. Don't give up. PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE stay safe, and enjoy your birthday! Here's to many more and all of the success that will meet you in the future. I love you!!! ğŸ˜˜ğŸ¥°ğŸ‘‘â¤ï¸ğŸˆğŸŠğŸ‚ğŸ‰ğŸ

author: @ayu_gyu
text: "Voices" is the song that introduced me to Stray Kids & I must say that it's such a perfect recommendation to introduce anyone to them. Other songs are amazing too but THIS had me feeling a lot of emotions. It was a rollercoaster ride starting from the catchy beats + the sad intro, to the powerful & impactful rap of Changbin (you'll immediately agree that they're one of the best in hip hop), to the vocal line's beautiful voices blended with Minho's mesmerising falsettos (pls his voice made me curious to know who's doing that part & led me to their profiles), to Hyunjin's unique rap style with emotions, to Han's rap which literally sounds as if he's shooting bullets with his mouth, to the dance break (pls that's still one of my favourite in the industry) & finally the ending with Felix's deep voice. Not to forget the overall lyrics are so relatable. Stray Kids came into my life like a blessing~ Always wish them the bestâ™¡

author: @binnie2165
text:
I don't think he's the only one who was helped by this song. 

I can't socialize easily, it scares me. But the evaluations at my school were exposing, I only prepared less than 1 day. I was like this for two weeks. I hardly slept, I was afraid of failing in front of all my classmates (many of whom were complete strangers to me), I was afraid of not getting a good grade, I was afraid of not finishing my presentations on time, and what scared me the most was speaking in public. But listening to SKZ I found this song, it was as if I felt relief every time I heard it. Before I went to school I would come to hear her every day..... I was a new student, so everyone was unknown to me and I never had that kind of evaluation.

Four years have passed since then. Now that I listen to Voices it is inevitable to remember those moments hahaha

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Hyunjin. It was certainly your musicality that drew me to you first. You have such a playful but easy tone which highlights and gives definition to every Stray Kids song. You donâ€™t have fixated or set rapping style. You are very experimental vocally and lyrically and Iâ€™ve found myself charmed by your voice due the versatility of it. I also love your singing style for similar reasons. You are just as diverse of a singer as you are rapper. It is really peaceful and harmonious; and blends perfectly with the rest of your members. I love how you donâ€™t hold anything back when youâ€™re singing and I can really feel the emotion and work that you pour into each line that you sing. Similarly to your singing and rapping, your body knows no limits when you are met with a choreography. You dance with a ferocity and a passion that no other performers can possess. You take each choreography and sincerely make it your own, which is honestly a blessing to watch. When you are dancing, you can be yourself and express your emotions with the beauty of your body movements. You can lose yourself easily into your dance and you are so comfortable and trusting of your own abilities. For this generation specifically, you have transformed music and given new meaning to what it can and should do for people. You are changing the world each day that you continue to share your artistry and dance; and we are so lucky to be alive right now to get to be a part of the history that youâ€™re making. At the same time that I love your music and dance, I love your personality as well. I love that sometimes you keep to yourself, but other times, you are goofy and outgoing. As I mentioned before, you are extremely freeing to be around and those who spend time with you can relax and be themselves in your presence. I know that nobody can attest to these qualities quite like your members. Seven different personalities, and they all love you and cherish you for their own special reasons. Theyâ€™ve looked to you and have modeled their perseverance off of how you strive to not let the difficult times hold you down and prevent you from success. You have opened your heart up to all seven people, although you come from different backgrounds, and that has encouraged them to all to have such a loving relationship with one another. Youâ€™ve had love for them since you began your journey with them and this has establishing a lifelong love that all of you had before you even debuted. You see the beauty and necessity of every single member and constantly remind them how important they are to Stray Kids. There is likely no greater feeling for them than knowing that they have you by their side if they donâ€™t have anything else. The most important takeaway is the time they spend with you and the way you make them feel, and these are both filled with warm memories they can take with them for the rest of their lives. Youâ€™ve already spent some of the happiest and life-changing moments of your life with them, and there is still more to come. The members of Stray Kids, also your brothers and your family, couldnâ€™t have somebody who loves them any more than you do to look after them. You are always so considerate of them and their feelings and respond to them however they need. They are the best versions of themselves because of you and because you love them just the way they are. Now, they can go on to do whatever they aspire to because youâ€™ve encouraged them with that confidence. I want to personally thank your parents and family for raising you and helping you become the person you are today. I know they mean a lot to you, and that you couldnâ€™t be here doing what you are without their love and support. Because of them, you can use your platform to share with the world the same love that they have provided you with your whole life. I hope you never forget that they are always going to be the most proud of you no matter what you do. They love you most in this world and they do so in a way that nobody else understands. Stay love them as you do and we keep them in our hearts as we continue our time with you. We are so grateful to them for bringing you into the world, and for changing the world the same way that you do. Hyunjin, you touch each individual heart of every Stay, and this is easily one of the most charming parts about you. It is in your nature to make each and every Stay feel special, even if you donâ€™t know us personally. You welcome Stay from all around the world with open arms, and I felt as if I was a part of the family my whole life. You are so dedicated to your Stay and this is very apparent in everything that you do, whether it be performing or communicating with us directly. You have so much compassion for Stay and I feel like we are existing in our own separate world with you. Although we all live in different areas across the world, you take us to a place where we can all be one big family together, and it is one of the greatest feelings in the world. What you give to us is irreplaceable, and there could never be another person who helps us see the worth in ourselves the way you do. You also help us love one another. You influence others to treat others with kindness and Iâ€™ve met some of the most heartwarming Stay. I know that you help this family become closer every single day, and you remind us that if we have nothing else, we have each other. You invite us into your heart, the same way that you do your members, and you see qualities in us that we donâ€™t even see ourselves. I know for a fact that there are Stay who only believe in themselves because of you. You also share so much of yourself with us, and this is perhaps one of the biggest ways you can show somebody that you trust. As time goes on, I notice you revealing more of yourself through your music and just through direct conversation with your Stay. You have gotten so personal with us and this lets us know just how much you actually believe in us and trust us to keep these parts of you within our hearts. There is no greater honor than to have you place this vulnerable side of you in our hands, and we want to do the same for you. I know that it is not always easy to do this, so I hope you know that we could never mislead you or betray your trust if we wanted to. You are one of the most generous people we know, and we could not be here giving love to others and to you without the love that you gave us first. I know that youâ€™ve been through a lot, both personally, and professionally, and that your time as an idol has not always been easy or enjoyable. Youâ€™ve been active for some time now, but during your training period alone, youâ€™ve been met with demanding expectations, which many people cannot even say theyâ€™ve undergone. Just as your family is, Stay could not be more proud of you from overcoming your hardships and making it out on the brighter side. Each time you are met with a grueling time or task, thought it make time, you eventually endure through it until the end, and become more experienced. As Stay, I can say we learn so much from how you choose to release stress or convey how youâ€™re feeling through the mediums that provide you comfort.  We are beyond proud of you and continue to learn from you each day. I hope that this birthday makes all of your dreams come true, and you can take the time to truly celebrate who you are as a person. I know it might be difficult to focus on yourself, and if you find this to be the case, I hope you leave it to those who surround you and your admiring fans from all across the world to help you realize how revolutionary of a person you are. You are truly a gifted musician, and a courteous and selfless individual. You deserve this day, and every day that follows, to feel as appreciated as you truly are. I hope that every second is filled with memories that are unforgettable, and that this will be one of the greatest days that youâ€™ve had! Please have fun and celebrate in whatever way you choose, because your Stay will be cheering with you!  Thank you for sacrificing your time, efforts, pain, doubt, fear, tears, emotions, and physical boundaries just to bring us any content at all. For every effort that you put in that you might think is small, a Stayâ€™s mood or day is completely changed for the better. You are blessing to this world and continue to change it every day with how you choose to heal it and the people living in it. I hope you donâ€™t overwork yourself because you are perfect just the way you present yourself to us. We will support you and be there for you for the rest of our lives! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future. Happy birthday Hyunjin, and we adore you so much!

author: @toomuchbuttah
text: omg no- this brings back sm memories TT i used to be OBSESSED with skz, they rlly were my everything at that one point of my life, and even tho i've moved on now and found my happiness with other groups, i will never forget how much they've helped me during that time of my life. i stopped being active with them for a year now, and even though i do have regrets, i feel like they'll be okay on their own for now. i've seen them grow and gained more fans and i'm happy for them, really. it's sad because i want to say "i'm reassured because ik with their bigger fandom, they are definitely safe and protected", but it was precisely because the fandom was toxic that i left it. ik that there are still many good stays out there, so i'm happy with that at least. even though i'm not really running alongside skz anymore, songs like these are what tugs on my heart strings and really make me miss those days. "voices" and "m.i.a." were the two songs that i really resonated with back then, and hearing them again after so long makes me feel nostalgia. idk if i'll return to the fandom anytime soon, but to the unproblematic stays, keep them safe for us all :) and even though i'm a bit sad that k-pop is unfair sometimes (the groups i stan now have smaller fanbases as compared to other newer groups), i'm truly happy for skz and their achievements. to see them expand in a matter of months made me proud. anyways, skz still has amazing songs so i'm not complaining :P and just because i hate the fandom, doesn't mean i can't still blast their songs like last time <3 thank you, skz, for everything.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: I.N.  You immediately stood out to me because of how seriously you take your role in the music of Stray Kids. I knew nothing about you when I first discovered Stray Kids, but from the music videos that I watched, you embodied the spirit and character of every Stray Kids concept so well that it left me speechless. You were the reason that every Stray Kids video felt like a mystery to me, and I found myself always wanting to know more. You blew me away from first sight because of how talented you are. You have one of the sweetest, most youthful sounding and powerful voices Iâ€™ve head. To have a voice like this is already unique, but again, you being so young is even more marvelous. You have this light and refreshing voice thatâ€™s capable of accomplishing so much. I always feel like Iâ€™m surprised when I hear it because each time you sing, you show your Stay a new side of you. When I hear you sing from one song to the next, I can feel your growth and am left stunned by the surprise of new elements that emerge from your vocal ability. I love that your voice fits easily with every type of Stray Kids song. Youâ€™re always experimenting with the different capabilities of your voice, but I love that you retain the classic sound and characteristics that personalize your voice. All the same, you are a gifted and expressive dancer. Your facial expressions successfully guide all of your dance numbers and completely dominate the essence of each performance. You move with such strength and determination. You really tell a story with your actions and your facial expressions when you hit the stage. I know that you want to give your audience every part of you and it is so clear to see when you put on a performance. You execute each move perfectly and your connection to the performance enlightens the experience for your Stay and your members alike.  Your movements are controlled and every detail is perfected. Overall, you are a musician who knows exactly how to make a statement each time that you perform. You donâ€™t just get on stage, but each time you do, itâ€™s unforgettable because you know how to speak to your audience members. Along with the individuality in your performance etiquette, I love your personality all the same. I first thought that you were quiet all of the time, but I learned that there is an extrovert that comes out of you when the momentâ€™s right. I love this about you because I know that so many people who can resonate with you on this. There are times when you are soft-spoken, and times where you have so much energy and communicate well with others. I love that the people close to you can understand you and are familiar with you in this way. Another trait that I noticed that you possessed with humor. Itâ€™s not often that I can see people make others laugh both intentionally and unintentionally. Even without saying much, you cause an uproar among your members and I know that this is part of the reason that they love interacting with you so much. They know you are capable of completely setting the mood for a great time or for turning their day around. I always find myself laughing at the silly things you say and the way you react to certain situations is always an opportunity to create happiness for your members. In general, I just love the relationship that you have with your members. You havenâ€™t been active for very long as a group, and I know you all have different personalities, but youâ€™ve fit right in with them since day one. You have this natural chemistry with them, and I know that they accept and love you just as you are. As I mentioned before, you donâ€™t even have to say much but you can ignite a spark of pure delight and joy when youâ€™re with them. It is so admirable that you have this ability to put a smile on somebodyâ€™s face so easily. Just by being around you, your members are automatically more relaxed and just carefree. I havenâ€™t even been a Stay for long, but I noticed almost instantly how sacred you are to them. They know you well enough already to respect you and understand you no matter how you choose to carry yourself. I can also see that youâ€™re almost like a human stuffed animal in that you provide so much comfort for them. Whenever theyâ€™re feeling down, worried, or just feel like being affection, they always turn to you to give their love. I find it sensational that they can rely on you or depend on you for always being there, simply because it is how you are naturally. You donâ€™t have to try, but you are such a kind and sweet person that you donâ€™t even have to use words to show it. We can tell by how much of yourself that you give to your members that you treasure them as much as they you. Youâ€™ve already left a lasting impact on Stray Kids as a group, but more importantly, youâ€™ve already changed the lives of each of your members individually. You were truly meant to know them and run into them because they are better human beings because of you. You still have so much of your journey left to go with them, and you are already creating memories that last a lifetime. I know that they couldnâ€™t love you more, and they canâ€™t wait to continue on together with you. Youâ€™ve already created a lifelong bond with each of them. I want to personally thank your family and parents for raising you and of course, helping you become who you are today. I know that your family are heavily responsible for the love you live know and are the reason you can give love so easily and abundantly as you do today. I know they mean the world to you and Stay are always rooting for them and appreciating them all the same! I hope you never forget that they are the most proud of you and never lose sight of them. Jeongin, you are the absolute source of laughter, light, happiness, and love for your Stay. I know you only get older, but as such a young age youâ€™ve already given so much love to the people that support you. Itâ€™s more than we could even imagine. Youâ€™ve worked so hard so far to give as much of your heart as you can to Stay and we couldnâ€™t ask for you to do more for us. Itâ€™s not easy to offer yourself to so many people as an outlet of entertainment and warmth, but you do it so earnestly without hesitation. I know that you really love your Stay and there is not an action in the world that you could take to prove that any further to us. You mean so much to so many people and you havenâ€™t even shown us all you can do yet. I hope that this helps you become aware of just how wonderful of a person you truly are. I often wonder what may be going through your mind, of what youâ€™re feeling because you always give your smile to Stay. You always want to appeal to us when youâ€™re most confident and selflEss, and doing this every day is the greatest way to show your love for others. I want you to know that in the little ways you communicate with us, you are showing us you care and value us enough to make us feel wanted and desired. This is all Stays could ever ask for. We feel your love each and every day and you donâ€™t have to do anything special to please us. We simply love your company and love that we always have you to turn to. We recognize how hard you work for us and how you become more considerate of us by the second. You are so honest and we never doubt your feelings or concerns because you are making the effort to be vulnerable with us. You show your love for us Stay in your own way and it could never be replaced or experienced in another form. I know that you have been through a lot in your life, both personally and professionally. Iâ€™ve seen some of the struggles and emotional moments youâ€™ve gone through both on and off stage, and they are really meaningful to see. It speaks to your character that you trust yourself and us enough to feel these feelings. You donâ€™t bottle them up, and when the time is right to express them, you do. I learn a lot from how honest you are to yourself, your members, and your Stay. I know that this has stayed consistent with you throughout your story so far, and I hope you never lose the ability to reflect on your own thoughts and feelings. I pray that this birthday brings you all of the blessings that you deserve. I hope you know how much there is for you and growing every single day around the world. There is not much that can be done with the pandemic going on, but I wish for you to be surrounded by the people who love you most and who can fill your heart with that love. Please enjoy your day and always remember the unconditional, unwavering love that your Stay will always have in their hearts for you. Thank you for all of the endless hours of practice, doubt, and hardships youâ€™ve endured to bring us anything piece of you. I can already tell that you take your work and your life so seriously and Stay can feel that passion. We are so grateful for what you do for us each day. Something that goes unnoticed to you has the power to change the life of at least one Stay forever. I am so proud of you for all that youâ€™ve overcome, and for never losing yourself Keeping faith and remaining positive is imperative to keep your head up another day, and youâ€™ve never lost that. You are inspirational, motivational, and extremely talented. You deserve all of your success and glory. I canâ€™t wait to see what you do next, and to see your dreams come true along with those of Stray Kids. You were meant to be where you are, and outstanding things are coming your way. Stay knows it! Thank you for all that you do. We love you so dearly. I pray that you and your family members stay healthy, and that you find happiness in the future. Keep shining Jeongin! You are absolutely beautiful! Happy birthday, and we adore you so much.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Minho. Deciding to support Stray Kids has been one of the best decisions Iâ€™ve made two years ago and in my life overall. I know that this year has been hard for most people, me included, but one of the only people continuing to give me hope is you. When I first got introduced to Stray Kids almost a few years ago, you were one of the first people that caught my attention. All of the members stood out to me, and for you, what I noticed first was your smile. When I watched my first ever Stray Kids video, it was simply your warm smile that immediately invited me in and made me want to get to know you and your members more. Last year, especially because we were all in quarantine, I have done exactly that. I spent a large amount of my free time getting to know you and become acquainted with your position on Stray Kids as well as your personality as an individual. What started with your smile led to me become captivated by your entire performance. Your sweet and versatile voice allows you to both sing and rap effortlessly and it always compliments every style of song that Stray Kids creates. Of course, your charm resides in your status are one of the most incredible and unmatchable dancers to ever exist. I have watched you dance in many different events and I can say I have never seen someone with as much control, whose movements flow naturally from one to the next, before you. You are an influential dancer and you tell a story every time you do so. Overall, you are an outstanding performer and an incredible musician and artist overall. You are a significant and vital part of the creation process of every single Stray Kids project, and it has been mesmerizing watching all of your songs and content come to life. Outside of your impressive performance etiquette, another reason that I have fallen more in love with you over the past year is because of your personality. I have come to know by watching various forms of Stray Kids content, and also from STAY, that you can be quiet in certain situations and donâ€™t always say much. However, you also have the ability to be very vocal and inclusive in any Stray Kids activities. There is so much beauty in that you donâ€™t even have to say much at all, but you mean so much to your members because when you do speak, what you say is either extremely meaningful or humorous. You always make your members laugh in the most unexpected moments and I have spent many joyous moments laughing alongside you, STAY, and your members because of your unique, spontaneous humor. On top of this, you speak your mind when it matters most and you always seem to have the most insightful words to give about the moment you are in. I have come to know that you are a person who is very aware of his surroundings and that you value your members very much. Because of this, there is beauty both in your silence, because you are an observant person, and in your words because they are always full of value and inspiration. I can see a lot of similarities from my personality to yours, and I know that that is one of the reasons why I gravitative towards you. You have offered me a lot of comfort and laughter over the past year and I wish that there was something that I can do personally to repay you for how grateful I am. However, I know that I am not the only person who feels this way. There are a lot of STAY around the world who have similar personality traits and respond to the world around them in the way that you do, and it makes each of them feel more confident and comfortable. Another reason that I came to respect you so much, as is the case with your other members, is because of STAY. They love you so much and look up to you for multiple different reasons. I have also seen, because of your unique personality that STAY are a group of people that can understand you in a way that nobody else can. I find the relationship that you have built with your STAY something that is so special and unbreakable. Similarly, I love the relationship that you have established with your members as well. I can tell how much your members love and appreciate you and they exercise this in many different ways regularly. I aspire to have a relationship with my friends that is like family in the same way that you have a relationship with your members. I want to personally thank your parents and family for being a key factor in your success and upbringing; both musically and personally. I know that they love you in a way that nobody else does and that they raised you and encouraged you to be as strong and generous as you are today. They are the most proud of you and support you the most! I know you have gone through so much already, more than many people can say that have, despite not being active for very long yet. The ways in which you have recovered and persevered through your hardships is very inspirational and serves as motivation for STAY everywhere to never give up. Lee Know, STAY are so proud of you and are absolutely grateful for everything that you have done for us this far, which is already more than we could ever ask for. I hope that you never change because we love and accept you exactly the way you are and take comfort in the persona that you present to us. Thank you for working so hard every day, even before debut, to bring us so much entertainment and life-changing music. You are so legendary in the music world and you will always be respected and admired as such. My only regret is not become a STAY sooner, but I know that the unconditional love I have for you now makes up for my absence. I canâ€™t wait to see what you do in the future and I hope that you continue to evolve, improve, and grow with Stray Kids and personally for your own sake. I hope that you continue to work to achieve all of your dreams and get as much out of life as you desire. I want to wish you, from the bottom of my heart and on behalf of your friends, STAY, members, and most importantly, your family, the most beautiful and magical birthday that you can have because you deserve it. May it be everything that you wish for and even better that that! Thank you for accepting me into such a loving family and STAY will always support you and be by your side no matter what happens. I pray that you remain in high spirits and great health, and that you and your loved ones find happiness and worth in everything that they do. Happy Birthday and we adore you!!!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Bang Chan. As Iâ€™ve frequently noted, I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade but I have never seen somebody like you in the musical field before. What you have been and are capable of, is absolutely untouchable and Iâ€™ve learned that there is nothing that can take the sincerity and passion out of your character. I will say, despite being a long-time fan of K-Pop, I didnâ€™t become a Stay until the beginning of last year. I donâ€™t know how I went so long without knowing or supporting Stray Kids sooner, but I am completely and utterly thrilled to be a Stay now. To this day I wouldnâ€™t know about Stray Kids if it werenâ€™t for the Stay. I heard so much conversation among the fans of Stray Kids about how fearless of a leader you were, and I became curious. Over the course of the past year, I have spent my free time, which I lately have a lot of, getting to know you and your members. It started with liking a few songs, but then Stay, who talk with so much praise about you and your members, convinced me to see what was lying beneath the meaning of your music. I began to watch Stray Kids content whenever and of whatever I could, and I gradually fell more in love with your performance and personality overall. I have come to know how passionate and dedicated you are and have always been to music and performing. Even before Stray Kids was officially formed and debuted, you had music in your heart and I can see that clearly every time that you go on stage with your members. Not only do you have a naturally beautiful voice evident of vocal capability and strength, but your dancing skills are rigid and flawless beyond words. Your presence on stage is nothing less than inspirational and you ground and center your members in a way that Iâ€™ve never seen before. You always bring everyone together and emit unity on and off the stage. Outside of your musical performances, however, I have gotten the pleasure of getting to know you and your personality. I donâ€™t even really know where to start by how touched I am at the positive impact you have already made on this world despite only being active with your members for just a few years so far. Before I became a Stay, I didnâ€™t know much about what Stray Kids had gone through to get where they are now; and I didnâ€™t know just how much you went through either. However, the loving Stay introduced me to how hard you worked individually to keep your membersâ€™ heads above water through the rigorous days of training, performing, and other events that swarmed you. I was, and still am absolutely mesmerized at what you have accomplished to make this group possible, and successful beyond its comprehension. Thanks to the Stay, I know that before Stray Kids even debuted, you formed an unbreakable and unique bond with each of the members as well as one together as a whole. You lift your members up with the emotional and motivational weight of all the words that youâ€™ve ever said to them. To know that there would be no Stray Kids without you makes me love you in a manner that is simply indescribable. I know that I, your members, and the Stay have so much respect and admiration for you because of everything that youâ€™ve done and overcome in just the beginning of your musical journey. I have gotten the honor of seeing at least some of the groupâ€™s history and how it came to be, and seeing how you were a huge part of that makes me appreciate having you in my life more than I did before. You have single-handedly helped carry this group to victory and done so much to ensure that you stay together. You have always kept your promise that you, in words that I once heard you say, â€œDonâ€™t leave anybody behind.â€ On top of leading your group to all of its success and glory, your are also humble and kind and always put them first. You sacrifice so much for your music, your members, and Stay and we recognize how hard you work day in and day out. You are so funny, clever, and know not to take life too seriously. At the same time you are professional, intelligent, respectful, and wise beyond your years. You are every bit qualified to be the leader that you are and I hope you never doubt your capability of doing that because Stay have seen you build something beautiful with your own two hands from the ground up. You never gave up even when the world encouraged you to and from that I find so much inspiration that I donâ€™t even know how how to thank you. All I do know is that your family and parents are the most proud of you and love you more than any of us do. I canâ€™t even imagine how strong they think you are for what youâ€™ve created. I donâ€™t want to put any more pressure or a burden on you, but so much would crash and burn without you and I hope that our love and support is enough to lift you up through your darkest times. You deserve so many blessings and praise. I just hope that you know your efforts are being recognized every second and that Stay, your members, and your family love you beyond words. I canâ€™t thank you enough for everything that youâ€™ve already done. You make Stay and your members feel so valued and desired and I know that only you can do that. I canâ€™t wait to see what you do next because I know that I couldnâ€™t leave you or stop supporting you if I tried. On behalf of your friends, Stay, members, and most importantly family, I pray that this birthday is filled with all of those blessings that you deserve and that itâ€™s everything that you desire. I pray that you and your loved ones remain in good good health and good faith, because the world is relying on it in order to fully heal and love each other. Happy birthday Bang Chan, and from the bottom of my heart, we absolutely adore you. You make Stray Kids all around the world stay.

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Felix. You have to be one of the biggest blessings on this Earth. I know that I crossed paths with Stray Kids for a reason, and I know you were one of those reasons. Before I even knew anything about Stray Kids, I knew about you. Two years ago, when I got my introduction to K-Pop and was beginning to like quite a few groups, I didnâ€™t know much about Stray Kids, but I did know about you. I couldnâ€™t go anywhere without hearing anybody talk about you, and that was what lead me into wanting to find out more about you, and your position in Stray Kids. I came into the fandom blindly, without knowing any of the names of the members, and relied on the Stay to tell me everything I needed to know about you. It was because of the intense loving fanbase that you have that I learned, in only a matter of days, what a rare talent you are. The depth of your voice combined with your passionate vocals is one of the most beautiful sounds I have ever heard. Your rapping and singing abilities are entirely specific to you and are so captivatingly intriguing, that I knew I loved you from the moment I first got introduced to you. You are so flexible with your voice and on the stage; and once I first got notice of how outstanding you are, I couldnâ€™t stop discovering what made you so enticing and lovable. You are so recognized and appreciated for your natural talent that word reached me about how special you are before I even got a chance to know who Stray Kids really were. Since then, I have been a Stay, and I can say that you are an individual that led me to become one. I have never seen someone with such a bright presence and spirit completely dominant on stage and create an environment so mysterious and energetic for so many people. You bring to music what nobody else can, and I am so happy you share that with all of your Stay when you could be doing something else. I see how happy that you make your members, and since I am a relatively new fan, I still have yet to learn everything that Stray Kids has been through in just the two short years that theyâ€™ve been active. However, I have already seen how much you have healed your members when they needed you the most and provided for Stay a support system that they can actually believe in. You are such a delight to be around and I get so happy just seeing your face these days, especially with all of the craziness thatâ€™s in the world. You have a strong-willed heart, and you are extremely kind, forgiving, and non-judgmental. I have loved becoming so acquainted with you and appreciating all of your hard work because you deserve it! You do so much for everyone, and I hope you know that you are so loved and Stay are so grateful to you for even the little things that you do every single day! Never give up and I hope you continue to be the person that uplifts Stay and your members! I know that no matter what happens, Stay will always support you and I canâ€™t tell you how much you really mean to all of us. Thank you so much for being such a kind and loving human being, and for accepting me and so many people into your family as Stay! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future. On behalf of your friends, members, Stay, and most importantly, your family, I want to wish you the most entertaining and enjoyable birthday ever! Felix, have fun, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, stay safe, Happy, Birthday, and WE LOVE YOU!!!!!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Jisung. Deciding to support Stray Kids has been one of the best decisions of my entire life, and you are one of the people who are the reason why I do so. I only just started supporting K-Pop groups two years ago, and I discovered so many groups because I had the time on my hands. However, since I graduated high school I have found I have been a lot busier and unfortunately havenâ€™t been able to dedicate my time to supporting these groups that I like. I didnâ€™t think that there was going to be any time left for me to support another group, but then you came along. My first experience from Stray Kids was the song â€˜Side Effects,â€™ and it fortunately was a song where I got to hear the vocal and rap blend of your versatile voice. Next, it was â€˜Boxer,â€™ which despite it being an upbeat song, almost moved to to tears because of how beautiful your voice sounded.  After that, I watched you on â€˜The Masked Singer,â€™ and I couldnâ€™t stop from there. I quickly learned that there is nothing that you canâ€™t do. You are a stunning vocalist, flexible rapper, and outstanding dancer. Overall, this allows for you to be one of the most exceptional performers that I, and other Stay, have ever come to know. I knew, right from the moment that I heard your voice, that I had to have more. I kept going, and since then, I have come to learn so much about you and the legacy that you have already left on music despite being only a few years old as a group. Stay is one of the most unique fandoms that I have been so fortunate to join, and I now know that you are one of the reasons why. I had always thought about Stray Kids as being such an active group and constantly releasing music and content to show how much Stay meant to them, only to find out that you have been such a huge part of that all along. I havenâ€™t even been a Stay for very long yet, but I already have seen the indescribable impact that you left on Stay. It is unlike anything that I have ever seen. I can see how happy, inspired, and desperate that Stay are to reciprocate every ounce of love that you give to them. When I became aware of this, I knew I had to be a part of it. You are so generous, honest, loyal, and possibly most importantly, I have seen you completely change the type of day someone is having just by setting the mood. Whether it be your members, or Stay, you always make sure that everyone is having the best day possible, even it means you have to sacrifice your mood for somebody else. Because you are just naturally funny and inclined to make everybody around you happy, you have an outlook on life that causes everybody you ever meet to be better and happier because of it all. As Iâ€™ve said, I havenâ€™t been a Stay for long at all, but on behalf of the other fans, I already canâ€™t even thank you enough for everything that you do every day. You have such a refreshing personality that we all need, especially at this time in the world. I hope that you never lose the innate kindness in your heart and actions; and I am so blessed to be able to thank you for all of it today. On behalf of Stay, who encouraged me to join them and showed me that there are no limits to your love, your members, who adore you quite possibly in a way that no other person can, and your friends and family, who we know are so proud of you, I want to wish you the happiest birthday ever Jisung! I pray that you and your l loved ones stay safe and find happiness and worth in the future. I am so proud of everything that you have accomplished and am so glad I get to see you grow each day now! PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE stay safe, and I hope you know how much we all absolutely love you so much!!! Be happy!!!

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Changbin, I know that your birthday is in a few days, but I have to celebrate early as I will be unable to then! I would like to talk about your musicality. Iâ€™ve never heard anybody rap like you, and I know I wonâ€™t hear anybody rap like you for the rest of my life. You have this growl, this grit, that is enough to supply every word you say with the perfect amount of power and character that it needs. No matter what the circumstance is for your song, you retain this originality and this sound that nobody else has. The connection between the raps you create and your execution of them is simply seamless.  Your lyrical style is mesmerizing, and watching these musical ideas pop into your head like second nature is truly astonishing. You can also sing beautifully as well, and the rough texture of your voice gives you this edge that lights up all of your lines. It is rare to see somebody be able to master both singing and rapping, and the unique sound of your voice allows for you to become limitless through both. You are also an incredibly skilled dancer. Your moves are so natural, and watching you feels surreal because you become so immersed in your movement. You absorb all of these choreographies, and then interpret them in such a realistic and emotional way. You have so much power and when you dance, yet you have the right amount of control to give off just the perfect amount of expression. You give care to each little gesture, and treat each move with such delicacy. It is a journey from start to finish when you dance, and you take all of us with you without missing a single detail along the way. Overall, you are one among other artists that sincerely represent our generation and capture its essence. Your innovation and relationship with music are so complex and clear at the same time. You are young, but as you become older and more experienced, there is no telling what youâ€™re already curious and inventive mind will supply to the world. Your impact on music and your Stay will be timeless. At the same time that I love your musicality, I love your personality as well. I first noticed that you are so laid-back and have this calming demeanor. You are also unexpectedly hilarious. You make jokes in moments where nobody anticipates and you can change the entire mood of a situation in mere seconds. You are so humble, and place those around you before you no matter what the circumstances. Though I have never met you in person, you have to be one of the best people to be around and I know that your members know this better than anybody else. You really hold your team down, and together, and always find a way to make sure everybody feels included. It has only been a short time since Iâ€™ve known you, but I saw almost instantly how your members individually love and cherish you in their own special way. You bring the excitement and thrill of life to them wherever and whenever they need it. You have the biggest heart. You have stood your members up time and time again and pointed them in the right direction if ever they forget what they are chasing after. You are somebody they can lean on through all instances in their life; and have become their brother. We all know that you provide your members with a love that they could not get from anybody else. Though they are all different, you find a way to embrace this and form a sacred relationship with each of them. I know that they will continue to grow and develop, but only with you by their side to guide them through it all. They will continue to be the best versions of themselves and there is nothing that can hold them back because you believe in them with all of your heart and soul. Your love will always trail them and aid them for the rest of their lives. Thank you for raising them, and changing their lives forever so that they can lead the fullest life possible. I want to personally thank your family and parents for raising you and helping you become the aspiring young man you are today. I know how much your family means to you, and you have firsthand showed us what they mean to you and how you spend your time with them. It is clear to see that you already keep this in mind with you at all times, but I just want to say that I hope you can always rely on them in your life when you find you need somebody. When you find yourself having troubles down the line, I hope you can remember the feeling of being with them to restore you to your former state of peace and optimism. Your family loves you more than anybody else on this planet, and I hope you know that when you feel there is nobody who can understand, they will always be there to help you out of any tough situation. They are the most proud of you, will always be the most proud of you, and you honor them with every step you take towards your dream. As Stay, we keep them in our hearts as you do and hope to become as dedicated and authentic through all that we do as they are. Changbin, it is often said that Stay are the luckiest fandom in the world, and I can wholeheartedly agree with that as you are responsible for the truth behind this. You are extremely sensitive and considerate of all of our feelings, and that is perhaps one of the aspects of you that I love the most. You seem to always listen to what we have to say and are even eager to respond to it. When discussing Stay with your members or others, you always have the most original ideas and show us how much you love us through your own eyes. When we chose to become a Stay, you chose us. Your world opened up to us and you invited us to become every bit of a part of you as your members and family.  Similarly to your members, there are Stay from all over the world who come from different backgrounds, and it is only because of you that we are able to come together in unity. I know itâ€™s not always easy to let us in and to see us while youâ€™re in a tough situation, but the fact that you put your fears aside and show up for us every time is the greatest testament of your love for us. You are the first person we turn to when we are down and need cheering up. It is truly the greatest honor getting to be the ones that you work so hard for and trust it all to. You have faith in us when we donâ€™t, and it gives us enough confidence to tackle whatever is thrown at us. Thank you for loving us unconditionally, and being there when nobody else has. Thank you for changing our lives, and being at the heart of the greatest days of our lives. I know that youâ€™ve been through a lot, and youâ€™ve only been active with Stray kids for a few mere years. Iâ€™ve seen firsthand how it took all you had and then some to even debut, and there have been too many struggles since then that youâ€™ve faced. The best that I can do, knowing that youâ€™ve been in these difficult situations more than anybody should be in, is try to imagine how it feels to be in your shoes. I know that itâ€™s been a lot. All that I can say, on behalf of all of your loved ones, that we are so proud of you for making it past all of these moments. You have a heart a gold and always keep your head up even when it feels impossible, and I know that this is the reason why youâ€™ve been able to persevere through all that youâ€™ve been through. Thank you for teaching us that we can do the same, and for having enough ability to force a fulfilled live for your Stay and members a well. We know that you can take charge and make it out of whatever happens in the future. I hope that this birthday makes all of your dreams come true and that you accmplish all that you desire on this special day. I often wonder of when you get to take a break and truly look back on the impact that youâ€™ve had on the world, so I hope that if anything, your special day provides you for the perfect opportunity to do that. I hope you are able to look at the countless hearts that you touch every day around the world in limitless ways, and let that make you feel as loved and honored as youâ€™ve ever felt. I hope that those around you also help you to see how worthy of love and commemoration that you truly are. Please relax today and I hope that you spend every second making precious memories. I hope that this day goes down as one of the greatest youâ€™ve had in a while. You deserve all of the sucess and blessings, and I know that more will only come to you. Thank you for sacrificing so much just to make Stray Kids and several other projects possible. Thank you for suffering through any pain, concern, fear, doubt, isolation, confusion, fatigue, stress, and so much more just to bring us any content at all. I hope that you never feel pressured or obligated to change because you are a rare gem of a human being. The world, and more specifically, your Stay need you just as you are to continue to inspire us and remind us what it is to love others and yourself in daily life. You are beautiful inside and out, and perfect as you are. I hope you remember we always will support you no matter what! I pray that you and your loved ones stay safe, and find happiness and worth in the future! Happy birthday Changbin, and we adore you so much!

author: @americanoooochoachoa4396
text:
Ahh yess the song that made me stan stray kids! I'm starting to remember the day I first stumbled upon skz performance video of god's menu while browsing yt. I don't remember much on how I became i stay actually, the only thing I remember was I started listening to some of Skz song and it got me interested. 

Back then I was struggling with low-self esteem, fear of talking, fear of mistakes, restlessness, fear of going outside and talking to people. I even often find myself lost and frustrated. Of course, talking to someone or asking for help would've  made things easier for me but I couldn't bring myself to do it due to fear. So I handled things on my own...

Looking back at my past, skz songs seriously helped me face through my hard times! Their songs are so comforting, some of their songs are also relatable, some are cheerful and fun, some gives me strength to face my problems. Skz songs are indeed one of a kind. 

Now, I'm currently improving myself, and I'm not struggling as much as before! :) 

Ty skz and stays!!! I'm so grateful to stumble upon skz!  There are a lot of things that I seriously wanna add but I can't bring myself to do it. Since I'm terrible at expressing. Plus, English isn't my native language.

Also, Ty for those who took their time on reading this! Have a nice day/night/noon/evening ğŸ˜†ğŸ˜Š

author: @sweetie1272
text:
This song talks about how people just talk and there comes a point in your life where you only hear their voices, cause they silence yours *"I can't hear my voices"*

The voices of others have already stayed in your head and it is difficult to take them out to listen to yourself, voices that only suffocate
Criticism, insults, scolding, hurtful words, everything is still there and annoying. Your own voice keeps trying to sound louder, you try to speak to yourself but it's impossible.

C. Channiefreckles

My first language is not English but..
Come on Stay, as Changbin says in his last verse, block those voices that just lie. *"Don't let them fool you, you know they're wrong"*
These guys produce and write all their songs. Stan stray kids, you won't regret it

author: @Amyafterhours
text: This song deserves so much more recognition & hype. Not only this one but their first 3 albums INCLUDING their predebut one 'Mixtape'. You really dont see "kpop" idols talk about stuff this straightforward or even incorporate it into their dance this "aggressively". Stray Kids are one of the few artist that that do that back to back and it coms from them genuinely. Songs like this are why I say they don't really fit the "kpop" genre. Not bc im trying to say they're "above" kpop or anything but because they really don't just make Korean pop music. They have so much diversity in their music whether it's in genre, chord progression, song structure, everything. If you dig into the technicalities, they're are so so unique and I just dont think labeling them as "kpop" is fitting, it never was. These boys are pushing boundaries to see how far they can go & I think thats what is going to give them even greater success. I'm so proud to support them, and excited to see what their new music will contain as far as content goes!

author: @faraheladawiyah
text:
Pertama kali denger tahun 2018 dan nggak ngerti arti lirik bahasa koreanya. Tapi dengerin lirik bahasa inggris sama emosi mereka, lagu ini dale banget. Langsung jatuh cinta. Padahal saya kira lagu barat yg dicover ke bahasa korea. Ternyata mmg lagu mereka sendiri. First impresaion yg sangat2 membekas. Dalam hati. "Saya harus mendukung musik mereka" 

Jadi, mereka pengalaman saya membeli album resmi KPop walau udh dengerin musik kpop dr 2004. Sampek sekarang album mereka terpajang di lemari. Itu sebagai bentuk apresiasi atas musik2 yg bisa menyentuh saya. Usia saya bukan untuk ngestan group ini itu. Tapi saya akan ttap mendudukung anak2 ini. 

Tetap semangat , nuna akan selalu mendukung kalian, apapun yg terjadi. Jangan pernah malu memperkenalkan karya kalian ke seluruh dunia. Jangan ubah gaya kalian hanya untuk menyenangkan orang lain. Tapi kalau gaya kalian berubah memang kalian ingin mencoba sesuatu yg baru nuna dukung kalian. :)

author: @dubuque2526
text:
Hello, I'm a new stay and let me share something:
I have social anxiety issues or that 'voice' whenever I try to talk to someone, including my friends and me. I always staying away from my friends to cry alone because there always an invisible voice saying I don't deserve to have friends, they are just pretending to be, and they secretly hate you for who you are. I always just thinking about negative things and problems that didn't even exist. I don't have the confidence and encouragement to talk about my problems to them because I felt I'm just a problematic boy who has problems literally with small things.

Then, that day. I don't even want to talk with them. I just zipped my mouth whenever they are messaging to our group. I just saw how happy their conversation without me. Whenever I try to join, the voice just keeps telling me that I will ruin the fun and they will hate me for joining the conversation. I don't know why I can't do it. I can't fight that voice and always ending up losing. I just end up crying almost every night thinking why am I like this? Why I can't be a normal person? Should I end here right now?

As I stan stray kids and hear this song. This masterpiece just saved me. When I heard the chorus, This gives me strength that I will do it.  I never ever felt to be free from these voices. It's felt like freedom. There are more things I want to do before I cut the last breath. So sooner or later, I will talk to my friends about my problems.

Thank you, Stray kids. Thank you so much for saving me from these voices inside of my head. I will support you until the end.

author: @meowyoi
text: it's already 5am in here and I just wanna say how this song always make me cry. this is the song I always listen the most when my dog died. She's the longest dog I've ever had. She had a single puppy, it's so tiny baby and suddenly it died. Because she wasn't feeding it well, I was trying to feed her puppy all by myself but when I was looking for materials that U need to use,when I came back to them,her puppy already died. she was crying, after that we bury her puppy. she was finding it all-day long. then there's this day when we taught she was gone, because she's out of nowhere in our home. It was raining outside but I still need to find her,but I haven't found her. then the next day she came back,after that she became so aggressive,she always fought with our other dogs. she always causes fights, then my family said that we should leave her on a abandon place because she might also bite us people. then my cousin and grandpa leave her on that place, later on we saw her walking to our house. she was so thirsty,she would cry again finding for her baby. we feel so bad for leaving her,we have no choice and we just let her stay to us. then on the night time I was watching SKZ contents,my cousin suddenly came to me saying that she already died. and I can't-.. she's the longest dog I've ever had. she and her baby along with her brother can rest in peace now. Thank you SKZ for calming me down and making me happy and warm until now.
