author: @alienhannie3322
text:
This comment is just about myself. You can keep scrolling.

This song made me join the fandom. When I heard "Voices" I cried. Maybe you can find it strange but yeah I cried so hard. I was know God's Menu and Victory Song but Voices made me a STAY while crying so hard. I am not regret. I'm proud with being a STAY. Beacuse our SKZ has songs like Glow, Grow Up, Mixtape #3, Voices... 

In daily life I'm a panicked person. I want to say somebody to me "Take it slow." and Seungmin says it in My Pace. 

I have sleeping problems and Insomnia helps me with Hyunjin's beatiful voice. 

I'm a hardworking student but I keep thinking about "Is it enough? Should I study more?" but when I think something like that Mixtape#3 helps me and says that I'm doing well. 

I am a asocial person I don't have so many friends and I don't have self-confidence too but when I listen Phobia I felt that I am not the only one. 

When I listen Slump I remember my old and peaceful memories. 

When I think that my teenager years are about to finish I listen 19 and get lost in the lyrics. 

I am that kind of person who runs so many thoughts in her head and 'm getting tired of myself when it happens I listen TMT. 

And so many things like that. Stray Kids' songs are just about me being myself. They making me feel that I am not the only one and I can keep going. I am so thankful them. Cuz you know even you have so many supportful people around you it sometimes become harder and you can't tell anybody... I don't know. It is different for me. Stray Kids is special for me. 

I am so glad to meeting them. They filled the emptiness in my life.

(Sorry English is not my first language. I just wanted wrote it in English because maybe one of them can read it :") )

text: the story of how I became a stay: I had a k-pop playlist randomly playing, (because I was to lazy to make my own playlist lol) and then this song came up and I was just listening , then I was like "damn who is this? their vocal are INSANE" and it just so happened this video just came out and it hadn't been that long since they debuted and I was shocked, so I searched them up and listened to more and more or their songs and I LOVE THEM SM, not only are their vocals and raps AMAZING and their choreography is CRAZY AWESOME, but they also send rlly relatable and helpful messages through there music. I started watching more of them and their hilarious crack videos and they're sooo funny. I have been a stay for a few years now and I'm so happy that I found them :D #ot8

Receta de mote con huesillo

Como ven les traigo una receta nuevamente y para no variar FÃCIL! un tÃ­pico postre chileno que no solo sirve como postre sino a cualquier hora del dÃ­a, idealmente en aquellos dÃ­as calurosos en donde la sed abunda.

Cabe decir que los huesillos son duraznos deshidratados con carozo. En algunas instancias se puede sustituir por la ciruela deshidratada, pero no es de gusto masivo como el huesillo.Y el mote es semilla de trigo.

 Tiempo de CocciÃ³n: 40 mins Tiempo Total: 40 mins Porciones: 4
INGREDIENTES

3/4 a 1 taza de azÃºcar morena

INSTRUCCIONES

Al siguiente dÃ­a, se ponen los huesillos con toda el agua en una olla, mÃ¡s el azÃºcar y la canela.
Se puede agregar chancaca si gustan, lo que le da el color al jugo. Otra opciÃ³n es que pueden acaramelizar un poco del azÃºcar para agregarla cuando el jugo aÃºn este caliente. Eso tambiÃ©n ayuda a dejar de color el jugo. Y sino simplemente lo agregan el azÃºcar al momento del inicio de la cocciÃ³n de los huesillos. Que puede que no quede del tÃ­pico color el jugo, pero quedarÃ¡ igual de sabroso. Eso se los aseguro.

Mientras tanto se cuecen por unos 20 minutos el mote con abundante agua. Luego de la cocciÃ³n hay que botar el agua con la ayuda de un colador. Dejar en una fuente que pueda ir al refrigerador. Reservar.
Una vez listo ambos ingredientes, servir bien helado en un vaso largo unas 2 a 3 cucharadas de mote, 2 huesillos y bastante jugo de los huesillos.

author: @riyamehta6795
text:
This song...

I donâ€™t think SKZ realise the amount of literal lives theyâ€™ve saved with their music. 
Before I first listened to this song, I wasnâ€™t exactly... happy. Constantly, there were so many people telling what to do, where to go, what not to do, what I should become. I was tired at just my teenage years.

I remember almost dropping my phone as this came on. I scrambled to look up the artist, and since then, Iâ€™ve not regretted clicking on this. Iâ€™ve been a STAY for just a year now, but you feel like family. Each and every stay seems so supportive and kind. 

Itâ€™s going to be difficult to convince everyone to let me walk on my own on another road, but songs like these will give me a shoulder to cry on and a friend to have when things are down.

Thank you, SKZ. Thank you, STAY. Youâ€™ve truly made me stay.

author: @aerisdl
text: This is actually a song that I really relate to. Its been 4 years since I started hearing voices in my head. It tried to control everything I do. It told me to do this and to do this. I felt like I was going insane. I lost friends and grew away from my family because of these stupid voices that told me to say this or do that. Its been harassing me. It makes me overthink and makes me change my decisions so much. I try to ignore them like I cant hear them. It tries to change me so much that I lost everyone and myself. This song kinda bring a lot of comfort to me and helps me alot. This song also helped me tell my family about the voices i keep hearing and Im currently in therapy rn. Thank u skz. Im gonna start being stay now:)

author: @goosegoose1.o929
text:
*V*TINGS* :
(Apps to download... some are of v*tings and some are for promotion ads)

1. IDOL CHAMP (for w1n on "Show Champion")

2. Mwave (for w1n on "MCountdown")

3. WhosFan (for w1n on "MCountdown" too)

4. MuBeat (for w1n on "Music Core" and promotion ads)

5. TheKkings (for birthday ads, group promotion ads)

6. FanPlus (for promotion ads)

*"Voting Tutorials"*

1. *"Show Champion"*

Download Idol Champ app andÂ follow this tutorial. Each person gets 3 votes per day. You can get red hearts by watching ads or completing missions and blue hearts by logging onto the app every day and answering quizzes.

2. *"M Countdown"*

V*ting can be done through either Mwave (website and app) and Whosfan. Download the Mwave or Whosfan app. If you have downloaded Whosfan,Â follow this tutorial! For Mwave, each person gets 1 v*te using one social media account. If you want to v*te for Stray Kids more, then use multiple social media accounts.

3. *"Music Core"*

Download the Mubeat app andÂ follow this tutorial. To get heart beats, go to store and watch ads or complete missions. V*ting is unlimited and you can use multiple social media accounts for more chances to v*te. You can start collecting heart beats now, the earlier you start, the more you can accumulate for voting later...

4. *"TheKking"*

Download TheKking app.
After you sign in youâ€™ll be directed to the homepage. From there you click the plus button next to the pink tokens.
Then you can watch ads to gain v*tes. You can watch 10 ads every hour and you get 5 tokens for each ad.Then click convert at the top and click the convert thing. Youâ€™ll be shown this convert thing and you just have to click the add point and convert. Every 10 tokens is equal to 1 vote. Then click the Group Vote then click the heart next to Stray Kids.

5. *"FanPlus"*

Download FanPlus..After you create an account youâ€™ll be directed to the home page. From there you click v*te at the bottom.Then youâ€™ll click free v*ting. You will watch ads. Each ad is worth 15 votes. Everyday you can watch 30 ads maximum. 

*"Pre-order Album"*

Buying albums can count on charts and music shows!

If you're from the US, consider buying from *Amazon* , *Walmart* ,
*Barnes* and *Noble* and *Choice Music LA* as it counts for both "Hanteo" and "Billboard charts" You can also buy merch along with a "digital copy" of the album.... This will count towards Billboard charts as well !!

( *Note* : Pre-orders from SubK counts for Hanteo and Gaon but do not count for Billboard..)

*"STRE@MING"*

Stre@m on Korean music platforms:Â 
*Genie* |Â  *Bugs*

Digital scores is one of the criteria for winning on music shows. 

*"Youtube Stre@ming Guide"*

Youtube vi*ws also count for music shows so it's important to accumulate as many vi*ws as possible during the time 

*"HOW TO STRE@M PROPERLY"*

1) Watch the video FROM THE FIRST UNTIL THE LAST SECOND! 

2) Watch the video in HD (720p, at least ) We are always trying to put it in higher quality. If u can afford stre@m in HD! if ur device hasn't HD or ur internet connection is low.. then 480p is allowed

3) DON'T skip, stop or rewind the video

4) The sound on your phone should be more then 50%, U can mute the sound on ur laptop and PC, but be sure that the volume on Youtube is more then 50%

5) Don't forget to leave comments and likes to not be considered as bot

6) STREAM MANUALLY! Don't use the playlists and loops when u have a free time for watching the videos on Youtube. Playlists and loops are the main reason of freezing the vi*ws for a long time..

(Remember that Youtube like to delete vi*ws..) (snake..bwkwhw)

7) DON'T USE multiple tabs or incognito mode - they are counted as SPAM and ur vi*ws will be deleted... 

8) DON'T SKIP THE ADS! They are counted as part of the video and if u will skip them.. you actually will skip the video and ur views will not counted by Youtube..

9) Don't change the speed of the video..

10) Use different browsers ( Mozilla Firefox, Opera, Google Chrome and etc ), accounts, internet connections ( Wi - Fi and mobile data ), devices ( PC, TV, phone, laptop ) for stre@ming of the videos.. these things will helping to increase the vi*ws...

11) AND NOW THERE IS THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE: you CAN'T REWATCH the same video again and again without any gaps!!!!!!!! If u will rewatch God Menu on repeat again and again.. Your vi*ws will be counted as SPAM and will be deleted....The gap among rewatching the same video should be 10 minutes or 2 other SKZ MVs in between.. 

FIGHTING STAYS 

*" Stre@ming on Naver is important "*

Stre@ming their music videos/music show performances helps in keeping Stray Kids trending onÂ Naver. Naver is South Korea's biggest search engine. 

Soooo... Stays 

â˜† Collect Red hearts on Idol Champ

â˜† For mwave and whosfan you don't need to collect or save anything.. when they will start promoting their songs.. We need to directly v*te.. (you can v*te 1 time per day so it would be better to create more accounts)

â˜† Collect heart beats on Mubeat ( it would be better if you'll use more than 1 account)

â˜† V*te for Seungmin.. he'll have subway ads for their b-day..(Also collect hearts for Oct Line)

â˜†V*tes for Oct line... on FanPlus..

LET'S BREAK MORE RECORDS... LET'S GETÂ  W1NS...

author: @essy_yu
text:
The thing is, Stray Kids taught me to accept myself.
In this world where everyone is pushing the agenda of loving yourself, somehow people have forgotten to remind us that the first step towards loving yourself is accepting yourself, all your flaws, weaknesses and demons. I found Stray Kids at a time when I hated everything about me,when I couldn't accept my lost and useless self. But after meeting these beautiful people, I've learnt to accept even myself,even my weak and lost self.
So thank you Stray Kids for making me STAY.
STRAY KIDS EVERYWHERE ALL AROUND THE WORLD.
YOU MAKE ME STAY

author: @Mari-hm7vc
text: I discovered Stray Kids a few weeks ago. A while ago, I was in the midst of a crisis, and this song started playing (I was listening to music to try to distract me) and then I started to calm down; I think something like this has never happened to me before; I found it incredible. Although I did not know very well what the lyrics of the song said, it reached me, and it reached me a lot. Just minutes before, a very, very strong feeling had come to me, that of doing you know what, but Stray Kids, this song, saved me. Literal. As "cheesy" as it sounds. I never imagined it would happen to me. Stray Kids have a place in my heart from now on. Even though they won't read this, I just wanted to leave it here.

author: @andthatsalongassride9587
text:
OK I know this sounds a bit cringe but, I had like a small panic attack once, it isn't anything like that what most people have been through and I feel kinda dumb writing this. It was on a normal day in my class, the teacher was sick or something I don't remember but  my class was so loud. Everything was booming and I couldn't help myself it reminded me of all  the times my parents had fighted and I couldn't do anything, I at some point had crouched down under my table, my head in my knees with my best friend beside me trying to comfort me. I don't clearly k ow why I had a panic attack at that point but I know there were voices haunting me. It was crazy and at the point I just wanted it to stop. Since then I hold great respect for the people that have to go through something like that everyday.

I hope everyone of you is alright, please stay healthy and remember no matter how dark the situation is there is always light even though you don't see this at first....

"Break free from the voices in my head"
Its hard. When i heard this song for the first time i was very suicidal and I couldn't help but cry. It was too overwhelming, this song that i could relate to a lot.  I discovered about this group called stray kids, and i couldnt stop but listening to it. Now its 1,5 years ago. The reason why I'm still here is them, they gave me happiness when i needed it the most. Thank you stray kids, thank you for everything you've done for me, i couldnt be more thankful <3

author: @Tyler_Not_Taylor
text:
Stray Kids - â€œVoicesâ€ Analysis
Overview: 
Overall very nice song, no reliance on autotune, canâ€™t hear any of it if it was used
Strong reliance on synth and bass, but acoustic guitar mainly used for rap section and transition, or by itself
â€œAhâ€ sound effect sparingly used in the background
Bass singer, when used, creates a f a t triple octave harmony
Choreography is godly, synchronized with music and beat
When rap sections are on, only shows one or two members, while in chorus sections, uses multiple dancers
Member singing at 1:30 is my favorite, his voice is much more r o b u s t
Intro:
Bass progression up and down F chord
Voice moving up and down F chord, alternating with bass for inverse harmony
Breathing sound effect emulates the theme of voices
Tempo ~ 80 BPM, 4/4 time
Rap Break:
Shift to ~ 140 BPM, shifts to cut time
Acoustic Guitar introduced into the background
Usage of synth classic dubstep in replacement of bass progression
Rapper moves in sync with chord progression, creating open harmony
Bass becomes stronger, to help reinforce synth
Transition Out: 
Slap synth doubles, chord begins to shift to augmented-major
Scoop up to perfect octave right before Chorus
Introduction to multiple English lyrics
Chorus: 
Background soprano octave reinforces open harmony, moving inversely from 8 - 7 - 6, alternating to 8 - 7 - 4, creating inverse and open harmony
Constant Synth beat repeated
â€œVoicesâ€ lyric becomes main repeated line
Concentrated lyrics at the end speed up the tempo, then stop when arriving at transition
Echo used for high voices, a good alternative to reverb
Transition Out:
2 new singer introduced, drastically changes tone because of the removal of echo
New lyrics thrown in but then shifts back to casual transition
Chorus: 
Almost the same as before, but new singers added
Stronger echo
â€œBreak free from the voicesâ€ line has removed echo, to symbolize the breaking away
Raindrop oscillating effect added in 
Drums are stronger
Transition Out:
Pretty much the same, reduced tempo
Many more English lyrics added to reinforce the central idea of the song
Rap Break:
Unique in that it shifts from person to person when rapping
Voice introduced in Transition Out gets added into the rap
Rapping stretches and compresses tempo
Synth Drop:
Big choreography moment
Synth becomes exposed, moving up and down 1 and 3 chords
Synth begins to scoop, unlike earlier
â€œVoicesâ€ line is emphasized in the background, echo is almost tripled
Ending:
Choreography becomes more and more centered towards the ground, with only 3 remaining standing at the end
Voice sound effect reintroduced from the beginning
R A T I N G : 9.5, very n i c e

author: @fairyqis0311
text:
That one time, there was butterflies in my stomach when i went for a drama audition for school. I was scared, scared of people's judgements, scared if im not doing well, scared if im lacking and cant meet the judges expectations, insecurities and that's really haunt me. But i keep playing this song in my head, as it says "break free from the voices in my head" and that's truly help a lot!  I overcomed it and somehow i felt proud of myself! Too bad, I didn't win the audition but i don't feel regret or sad at all, I think it's my first time not listening to those bad 'voices' and i told myself "do as you practiced without regret and give it all out". Then, turned out that i didn't win, rather than feeling sad i feel happy instead bcs i managed to ignore those 'voices'! 

THANKS FOR THOSE WHO READ THIS, I TRULY APPRECIATE IT! AND THANKS TO STRAY KIDS, I GOT TO OVERCOME MY FEAR â¤â¤ğŸ˜˜

author: @bratz736
text:
*Ngl this song gives me a weird vibe at **0:01**. It also kinda gives me a headache (in a good way) and this song makes me cry cuz I feel their pain. Idk if i can say i'm depressed but eh. I've always had this feeling that my father never loved me. He never took care of me when I was child. I rarely see him on Sundays and if i do, we either hang out with his friends. And I'm done wasting my tears for him. People at my school make fun of me cuz my mom has tattoos and says that i'm not Christian even tho I am. I have/had bitchy friends who judged me for who i am (and fake friends). Boys at my school call me gay and "mistake" me as a boy even tho I'm a girl. This song just calms me down and lets my emotions out since I have nobody to talk to. (and other SKZ songs) Worst part is that I was crying typing this.*

author: @napofeternity3477
text:
You're tired. You've been walking in this endless dark room for hours. Days. You're weak, and walk on shattered glass. You haven't stopped walking, yet you feel no pain as the shards rip you apart. There's a slight echo in the distance, so dim that you can't tell what it says, yet so loud that you can't hear anything, not even yourself. You feel you've become an object in this world, and the pain you feel matters nothing. Because no matter what you feel inside, you're always wrong.
This isn't true. Every person has a beautiful soul filled with the passion of a million stars. Follow your dreams.

author: @SleepEludesMe647
text:
It needs to be said: Woojin, your opening here was what made me interested in Stray Kids. Iâ€™ll always say that M.I.A is my favourite track and MV, that I AM You is the title track that meant the most to me, and that Tomorrow, Today is my favourite SKZ PLAYER. You did so well in those, maybe I appreciated them all the more because I could hear more from you, the one who, in those make-it-or-break-it seconds for someone to judge if a song that seems to outside of their comfort zone, if a group that seems to be outside their preferred genres and styles, could move and awe me with their music. I have you to thank for opening the world of Stray Kids to me, and Iâ€™ll always come back here to remember what that was like. 

I donâ€™t know what youâ€™re going through right now, only that it canâ€™t have been easy, but I will do what I can to support you wherever you may go. We are proud to have been there to watch you on your journey with Stray Kids. Thank you for everything you have done for us, and for them. #ThankYouWoojin

author: @SilentxForever
text:
It just hurts because there are so many people telling me what to do with my life. I don't know what to do because I don't even know what I WANT.
I feel so unmotivated and useless now because of it. I was supposed to be the one that had a set future. And here it is now, in crumbles because people voiced their own wishes.
I'm stagnant. Not doing anything because I don't want to disappoint anybody, but most importantly, myself. I don't want to regret my choice, so I don't choose anything.
I don't think the voices will leave my head anytime soon.
My head hurts.

author: @paigieinu1988
text: the first time i listened to this song was maybe at the start of this year. iâ€™ve read many comments from people saying that they suffer from things like anxiety and depression, like me, who suffers from anxiety, but i never found much comfort in that. despite knowing i wasnâ€™t the only one, those people didnâ€™t know me, i didnâ€™t know them so it felt just as lonely. stray kids are even further away than that, yet this song made me feel so emotional, and for the first time i didnâ€™t feel so empty and on the edge. they care. they know how it feels. they are there for you. i started to put myself in those peopleâ€™s shoes, and even though i still didnâ€™t know them, i think i finally understood how hard it is to convey your emotions and feelings. iâ€™ve never been more proud to be in a fandom, iâ€™m still amazed at how emotional i felt. honestly, i donâ€™t think iâ€™ll ever get over my anxiety, but now i think i can cope with it better. to all those people i still donâ€™t know, but understand a little better: thank you, and i hope you are doing well. <3 this video is a little older, but i just wanted to get this off my chest :)

author: @namgan_S3
text:
Sometimes you need to close your ears and trust your heart to walk towards your own path... No matter what parents, friends, or other people tell you how you are supposed to live in order to succeed in life, even if it would risk you to leave everything behind, you need to follow your dream and passion...


I'm in nursing school right now and the only reason why I'm in nursing school is to have a stable job... I tried to convince myself that nursing is meaningful job that helps other people but to be honest, my motivation was not "helping other people," but "making a living." I was scared to follow my dream and study what I really want to study because I thought it would be very financially insecure... But I JUST CANNOT DO IT JUST TO MAKE A LIVING... Isn't it life more than making a living?


...and there are so many VOICES in my head... and staring eyes...

author: @adrianna9678
text:
A Long Message About How K-Pop Affected My Life:
* This goes to everyone that thinks I'm weird for liking K-Pop, you guys have no idea how much K-Pop affected my life. Let's talk about the time before I discovered, I was really depressed, had so much insecurities about myself and etc. I was bullied in elementary and Abused at home, to made it worse for me, my papa was suffering from a type of lung cancer, all at the age of 5. I've been suicidal at the age of 8 till the age of 13. I'm 14 right now. But one day I've discovered K-Pop by accident, it was bts but then I started to open up to more groups. On the other hand, K-Pop/Groups has thought me so much then any other genre or artist had. Some of their songs thought me how to love myself, appreciate others and what I have, adore the small things in life, friendship is one of the most powerful things a human can ever had, how to be mature, how to get over my depression, that its alright to have insecurities ans that everyone has their flaws and that I'm not alone, I should reach out for help and that no one is gonna judge me for asking for help. Like this song "Voices" "get the voice out of my head" I could relate to that on a whole another level its crazy.. but eventually I did learn how to get the voices out of my head. Thanks to K-Pop I wouldn't probably be here right now. Thank You. *

*You are not alone in this world*
*You can do this, WE can do this*

author: @jackybaduria806
text:
For me, whenever I listen to this song, it always reminds me of how someone is speaking to us, someone bad, someone who wants to ruin our life, someone who wants to destroy everything about us. And that is the devil. Whenever there is something you shouldn't be doing, maybe something that's really bad, or maybe a temptation to just do that thing, then that's the devil's voice. That means you are listening to the devil's voice. Even giving up on something was because of the devil. Try to listen to the Lord and he will help you find your way out. Something good will come out of that. And here is Stray Kids always reminding us to keep going no matter how hard it is, and no matter what struggles you may have to face. Remember there is no success without struggles, so face it. If you have the passion to achieve something, do it. Don't give up. Don't let the devil win. That won't do no good. Don't rush. Just keep it at your own pace. It's better to let yourself gradually grow rather than succeeding right away. So have patience. In your own pace, you can learn new things and improve yourself more. To the 1% people reading this, never give up. Don't rush. Just go on your own pace. One day you will reach your goal:) I believe in you all! I love you SKZ & STAYâ¤

Thank you so much, Stray Kids, for always comforting us with these deep and meaningful lyrics. Something you are going through, that's what you tell in your songs. You tell your story through your music. We know what you're going through. That's struggles and us STAYs can really relate to you guys. These songs really help us through whatever we're going through and I just want to give you all my gratitude back to you! I appreciate it so much! Facing similar issues, we can just, you know, figure it out together, right? We can work together as a team, right? We can do everything together! We can help each other whenever we need it. STAY & SKZ is the best! We are not a fandom, we are a familyâ¤

_"You know, whenever you guys are having a hard time, feel depressed, or got a lot on your mind, just wanna say that, you know, it's always ok to come to us. Come to me, come to Stray Kids and tell us how you feel. Tell us what you're feeling. Cause, you know, we have ears to listen to. We will listen to you guys. And no matter what, we will try to help out with what you're going through. Because I think that's one thing that everyone in Stray Kids can agree on. We will always try to fix you guys. So, if you guys have anything, you know, come find us. We'll help you out."_ â€” Bang Chan (2019 April 14)â¤

*Bang Chan, Kim Woojin, Lee Minho, Seo Changbin, Hwang Hyunjin, Han Jisung, Lee Felix, Kim Seungmin, Yang Jeongin:*
_"You know, whenever you guys are having a hard time, feel depressed, or got a lot on your mind, just wanna say that, you know, it's always ok to come to us. Come to me, come to STAY and tell us how you feel. Remember we are always here to try our best to help you guys through whatever you're going through. We will always be there for you guys no matter happens. We will try our best to try to fix you guys. Just tell us, you know, we'll always be here to help, remember that._ â€” STAYâ¤

*_Let's keep flying high together!_*
*_Let's keep cherishing every moment of our lives together!_* 
*_SKZ & STAY FightingğŸ’ª_*

author: @momoabels6898
text: I feel like what sets them apart from so many other groups is the fact they write their own lyrics about things that are important to them. Not only do they put so much effort into all their performances but the fact they write their songs about things that matter to them or in order to help others puts so much more emotion and passion into them. Itâ€™s amazing. And not to compare them, but they only other group who has ever been able to make me cry like this through their music is BTS. And I feel like that says something. Again Iâ€™m not trying to compare them to BTS bc every group is different. But I feel like the fact they write about things that are important to them helps sooo much. Iâ€™m sure itâ€™s easy for someone to write a song about something fun and whatever, but itâ€™s harder and more emotional to write a song about topics usually that no one is willing to address. And to make it feel so sincere, you know theyâ€™ve had to have gone through it too.

author: @almostidioticgirl
text: Am I the only one who think that this is Stray Kids' best song from pre-debut until Miroh? This song just gives me chills from the get-go, the intro is strumming my heartstrings with sadness. There are just so many feelings in this song, in their choreo, in how they sing it. How Woojin opened the song with despair, then Changbin exploded with frustration, Chan screaming to break out, the pain for not being able to do so in Felix's strained voice, and Lee Know's defeated sigh. They even fell on their knees at his part. At the end Chan and Woojin are no longer screaming, but it's like a desperate plea, and closed by Felix's quiet surrender. The progress of this song is so emotionally draining, and I love it so much. The only other song I've heard that brought me through the journey of feelings is Day6's I Need Somebody. Of course I feel other songs too, but it usually just one kind of feeling. The two songs though, they're epic ğŸ˜

author: @atinymoon
text:
This was the song that made me stan these beautiful biscuits.
The lyrics hit me so hard since I got them basically in two ways. 
First is that I was bullied really badly for 4 years and people talked a lot bad stuff about me. Rumors, saying mean things, sending mean messages... It made me stop hearing my own voice. All I heard, were the disrespectful and mean things that others told to me.
Then the second way is that, after those 4 years, my own mind started to tell me all these things. I was so lost and couldn't hear the voice inside of me, the encouraging and sweet things all disappeared. Still, to this day I fight with my own self, but this song makes me feel like I'm not alone.
So stay, who are struggling, you're not alone. We have each other and we have Stray Kids.

author: @abigailroberts6925
text:
I don't get how people can dislike this song or the video,their literally talking about serious mental health issues like depression,anxiety etc. This is one of their more serious songs with a serious message and meaning behind it. They know that a lot of their fans have mental illnesses and their saying to just not worry about the voices in your head and that the bad times are just bad times and that there is always light at the end of the tunnel and you will get through it if you don't give up. Their there to help you get through those bad times through their music as channie always says. Stray Kids are always trying to be funny and caring for their fans even though we all know they go through these rough patches as well whether it's by individually or as a team. They are so caring,kind,grateful and lovely to their fans because were the same to them and they know that we love them to. I just really wish people would look at the lyrics and listen to the way there singing some of there parts because this is a message they really wanted to get across to all their fans that might be going through a rough patch or a rough time in their life 

I'm so sorry that this was so long and I'm grateful to anyone who read it all I just want people to see past their good looks and music videos to see the true meaning behind their music 
STAY forever 
Stray Kids fighting

author: @queenz2415
text: Y'know sometimes I feel like pounding my head into a wall because of how angry I get and how hard things get. My art has started deteriorating because I stopped for a long time and I still love art so much. Writing used to be my favorite too but I barely do that anymore either. All of this plus school and having to accept the fact that I'm growing up and will have to leave my parents in like two years always leaves me upset and angry. Knowing how short time is and how little time there is really gets me down. I feel like I've got the message wrong in this song but whenever I listen to it I feel like it's speaking to me. Like it understands everything that frustrates and upsets me and tells me to put it all behind me and love being myself. Thank you Stray Kidz :')

author: @diniwiradinata
text: Ok yes, my depression has told me several stuff like 'you don't matter.' 'no one loves you' 'theyll never be able to help you, so why reach out for help?' and stuff like that, but I feel like this song represents my intrusive thoughts more. I really don't want to describe them, but if I could find the best way to describe how I _feel_ about them is just helplessnes. I'm drowning in all the voices and I just feel so helpless, so weak, so tired. Their dance; where they sorta bend down on one knee, represents how I feel. Just tired. As if I've been knocked down. And when chan helplessly and tiredly said 'theres so many voices', I felt that too. If I could say something in the middle of my intrusive thoughts, it'll probably be that. All I can say is that I'm very thankful that stray kids made this song and reached out to me and many other people. Stray kids fighting~!

Listening to this song lightens up my mood a bit. I'm just so frustrated by everyone around me who expects me to live up to their expectations, be a flawless student, have excellent grades, get a scholarship (which I'm trying to get but haven't receive a response to my application in weeks). I'm sick of it all. Not to mention i've been feeling burned out and my grades are starting to get average. author: @Alex-vs5dh
text:
After about 2 years of Seventeen being my ultimate group, I think Stray Kids have replaced them. 

Their music calms me down or makes me just smile and want to dance (depends on the song) and every single member is incredible in their own way. They all make me feel happy and incredibly loved, even if Iâ€™ve never met them. 


Being Chan biased, his live-streams started at a time when I couldnâ€™t have needed them more. Between college, money problems, a breakup and stressing about my sister, my mental health went downhill quickly and nothing was helping. However his live-streams have honestly helped me so much. just have a short period of time every week where I can interact with others dealing with similar issues, and an incredibly kind soul with a fantastic music taste helps me so much. I enjoy just knowing Iâ€™m connected to so many different people who are all inspired by the same people I am. 

Thank you Stray Kids, for giving us such incredible music and making us feel like everything will be ok. 

And thank you to all the other Stayâ€™s! Everyone Iâ€™ve talked to has been so kind and I canâ€™t thank you enough. I am so proud to be part of this incredible family

author: @channiesroom5825
text:
My best friend recently got in a car accident and unfortunately did not survive the crash. Its devastating, and there's some vital piece of me missing without him here with me but this music, Stray Kids music is helping me through it. I don't want to be one of those who write depressing comments but I'm gonna do it just once because its weighing on my mind


3:40 am in the morning and my friend died. I was talking to him like 30 minutes before - its been about 2 weeks and constantly there are voices in the back of my head telling me that there was something I could have done, I left him on read cuz I fell asleep-if I hadn't could I have done something? Could he still be here? The voices whisper his name all the time and everything reminds me of him somehow, Chan's part when he says 'There's so many voices' so brokenly speaks so many volumes its uncanny - this song, it means something to me, to everyone - it help to distract me, to give me hope and reassure me its not the end of everything


I am glad to be a Stay. I am glad to have Stray Kids with me, giving me encouragement and songs that speak to me on levels I have never experienced before. It is hard right now, but thanks to them I know I will get through it. 
Thank you Stray Kids, you make us Stay<3

author: @annalynefrazer4330
text: I commented something in My Pace and I thought I should just say this here too after a reccomendation. I want to say how powerful and meaningful this song is for me because I've been struggling and drowning in voices I never wished for and no one seems to understand. This song not only depicted how I feel perfectly, but it also gave me encouragement towards the end. I am not a stay but after seeing the meaning behind theirs songs, I feel like I really can stay. In a world where you can feel really alone, music can embrace and accompany you. Stay Kids-- their music became that embrace I've been longing for and I feel like they're able to voice out things I can only dream of saying. I hope they get more recognition. I hope more people realise how powerful these songs are-- how talented these boys are.

author: @shaniaturner7571
text:
0:15, 0:59, 1:54, 2:07 {white shirt, tan pants} *Kim Woojin* [stage name: Woojin] (main vocalist, underrated vocals loves his chicken, nickname is bear, '97 liner, oldest)
0:28, 2:22, 2:48 {white shirt, tan jacket, brown pants} *Seo Changbin* [stage name: Changbin] (main rapper, vocalist, producer, 1/3 of 3RACHA who writes, composes, and produces Stray Kids' music [was formed in 2013], '99 liner)
0:40, 1:03, 2:10 {white shirt, pants, jacket, headband} *Kim Seungmin* [stage name: Seungmin] (lead vocalist, vocals are pure sunshine, nickname is puppy because of his facial features, '00 liner)
0:45, 1:09, 1:52, 2:15 {white shirt, speckled black jacket} *Lee Felix/Yongbok* [stage name: Felix] (lead dancer, lead rapper, don't underestimate his vocals, half of the Aussie line, was born in Sydney Australia but has Korean parents, '00 liner)
0:48, 1:16, 1:34, 2:23, 2:40 {brown short sleeves on top of white long sleeves with blue spots, brown shorts, blonde} *Han Jisung* [stage name: Han] (main rapper, lead vocalist, producer, 1/3 of 3RACHA, multitalented king, nickname is squirrel because of his facial features and the fact he stuffs his cheeks with food when he eats, '00 liner)
0:52, 2:00, 2:50 {white short sleeves, black speckled pants} *Bang Chan/Chris* [stage name: Chan] (leader, lead vocalist, lead dancer, rapper, producer, last member of 3RACHA, other half of the Aussie line, moved to Australia when he was young, loves the other members and fans very much, '97 liner)
0:55, 1:48, 2:04 (standing in middle) {greyish/greenish long sleeves, white pants} *Yang Jeongin* [stage name: I.N.] (vocalist, maknae, a literal baby, used to have braces but recently had them removed, nickname is fox, '01 liner)
1:05, 1:11, 1:21, 2:19 {white long sleeves, black vest, striped pants} *Hwang Hyunjin* [stage name: Hyunjin] (main dancer, lead rapper, visual, can be cute and rude, sometimes at the same time, '00 liner)
2:26 {white long sleeves, black speckled with white jacket, black pants with chain on the left hip} *Lee Minho* [stage name: Lee Know, sometimes shortened to Lino] (main dancer, vocalist, rapper, was a backup dancer with BTS on their Wings Trilogy tour, '98 liner)

author: @madlala6618
text: hello stays! i would like to bring attention to another wonderful stay, isaac. his channel is isaacskz (https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCz9eswAEaSn6VqubtSBMatg) his dream was to be the best stray kids editing account, and sadly he passed away from a brain tumour. however, us stays want to remember him and thank him for all the hard work, so if you can please watch his videos! they're truly amazing and you won't regret it. we are trying to spread love for him! you can check out #youdidwellisaac, #isaacandministaystrong, #skzxisaac on IG, and you will see he means so much to us. he worked very hard to edit for us. he used to have an instagram fan account, but it is now deleted. the recent videos on his channel also has his last words to us and his sister (@forhanjisung)'s letter for us. thank you for reading <3 he always said he's literally GIVING the edits for us, and it would mean a lot to isaac if we were able to enjoy them! so i'd like stays who havent seen them to check them out! he also said to support each other and the boys and that's the most precious part about isaac! please read his letter https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tc8xGGRHDFk (and here is his sisters: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XrUn7WGO-w0)

author: @thegoinggmerry
text:
This song is really something I can relate to. To hear Chan say "There's so many voices", almost helpless and defeated, kills me. I'm going through really tough times at my house and I constantly feel so much stress and pressure that it makes me paranoid. My situation at my small apartment with my family is confusing. Not to mention that I'm bisexual and my grandparents are homophobic. I always felt lost and without purpose and it hurts. It hurts so badly, to have a voice in the back of your head telling you that you're not loved. That you're hideous. That you're a failure. That your friends think that you're annoying. Oh, and I don't blame my friend for thinking this way, but one of my friends does think that. So music like this is really moving for me. Its like the glue that holds my broken and sometimes useless thoughts together. Thanks to the people who actually read this whole thing btw please don't hurt yourself. Please don't starve yourself. Don't hate yourself. Don't convince yourself that you don't matter like I have. Have an amazing day ^^

Edit: WHOA I never thought that one of my comments would become so popular thank you for liking my comment ^^
Another edit: oml y'all are so supportive ty so much y'all

author: @majal3684
text:
dear woojin, hyunjin, chan, jeongin, minho, jisung, changbin, felix and seungmin,
for the 1% chance that you're gonna read this one day, i just want to tell you that i cried when i listened to this.

i was an army for 2 years already and i didn't think i could ever feel as much love towards an artist like i feel towards bts, just because their music is healing, real and i can relate to them. but thanks to one of my best friends she said i should listen to get cool and n/s because she liked these songs at that time. so i listened to them. i really liked get cool but i wasn't that much into n/s. i listened to my pace before but i didn't listened to the lyrics so i didn't really cared about it. but 11 days ago, it was the 26th december 2018. i was alone at home and began to watch some videos. i immediately fell in love with all of you. I wanted to know more, so i watched several guide videos and after one hour i knew your names xddd then i watched so many mvs and guides that day late into the night. i listened to your music on spotify and the next day i immediately printed photos of you for my kpop journal. only two days after stanning you, you already were my ult group with bts and i've been binging your vids since then. I just want to thank you for healing with your music, for helping people who are struggling, for making such inspirational music and for being the persons who you are. i never ever would've thought to fall in love with a kpop group once again like with bts 2 years ago, but it happened and i'm so thankful for that and i will love you forever even when i haven't walked the path with you together from the very beginning.

text: okay, i know that they didn't write this song about ocd, but i can really relate to every word in this song. constantly, there are voices in my head; not the schizophrenia type, i can't hear other people. but it's my own voice, commanding me like a lifeless puppet. lifeless, because, i don't care about my health. don't eat, even if you're losing weight and it's scaring you that you can see your ribs, even in dim light. whisper a set of fragile words, like a charm, or your mom will be dead by morning. just like your dad. *don't* even think about going to that party; what if someone gets sick? don't call school sick. you aren't sick, you're just scared. like the coward you are. or maybe you are sick. maybe you need a mental facility, you nut job. who gets this scared? who touches each side of the wall so it'll feel right? who uses clorox wipes to wash their phone off every day? who can't listen to the tv unless the volume is on a multiple of five? _me. i do._ that's right. you're just crazy. _crazy?_ *crazy.*

author: @laratoya7088
text:
i can relate far too much to this song and i can tell im about to do the tmi thing but ill be brief
i am a sufferer from depression. it sucks, yeah, and i still have it. ive had it since i was 8 and am now almost sixteen. ive had ups and downs, and am slowly recovering but i do have some i guess side effects from the deeper parts of it. i reached one of the lowest points about 2 years ago now, and ever since ive experienced almost daily intrusive thoughts id guess youd call them - not exactly words as such, but pressing voicelike sounds in my head that i cant get to go away and can come at random times. when i have an episode like this, it can be extremely difficult for me to concentrate and i often have to try and force my mind to move onto another train of thought which can take any length of time from ten minutes to an hour. 
at other times there are distinguishable words, which give the vibe of basically the world being a hellhole and no one would miss me or alternatively more anxiety based e.g. everythings going to slow, speed uo, you cant help it etc.
but yeah i just relate a lot to this song as it is a constant battle with the voices in my head i guess. 
if you struggle with anything similar, i often find that listening to music can help, or thinking about your favourite movie. i sometimes stop what im doing and as im quite a musical person, pick a random song and try to work out the time signature and i do that until i can fully focus. not the most effective but it will go away on its own

wow that wasnt as brief as i thought itd be sorry ğŸ˜‚

We have these rules we want you to know and follow:

author: @mjs1278
text:
Their mask at the end ended me. It's such a powerful message for me, even tho i don't get what is the link with the song. But to me, their masks represent how i am unable to talk about my problems to my close ones. I know that you can still talk with a mask like they have, but it kinda show how i mute myself, because i don't know who would listen and who i should talk to. 

I don't have any diagnosited (fuck i can't even spell it) problem, but i am pretty sure i had depression a few years ago and contemplated suicide a few times too, along with self-harm and food disorders. To me, the theme of the song only reminds me of the voices of others that i imagine and that are killing me from the inside, and this little voice always here to tell me i'm a failure. And..idk, the whole song + masks mean a lot to me and i don't even know why i wrote this haha.. 
Anyway, i just want Stray Kids to be happy and treated like human beings.

I was always a stay and always will be, and at the time my anxiety got too much for me to handle, and my mom took me for help. They said with the voices I hear and see I could be schizophrenic. Here I am, on my way to recovery...and even though I heard this song many times before, I never actually listened. I cried and I am crying as I type this out. So thank you Stray Kids, for being there for me and giving me songs to listen to that I can relate to. Thank you Stray Kids, because if it weren't for these lyrics that you have given me, I may not have been here today. â™¥ï¸

author: @lee3561
text:
not to be dramatic but they've honestly been the only thing that kept me going recently. i don't want to know where i would be now if it wasn't for this group of incredibly talented, goofy, lovable human beings. this song makes me cry because it reminds me of the times where i've been at my absolute lowest, and the voices were the only thing i had; they were the only ones there when i'd cry myself to sleep, when i'd think about the future, and when all i did was simply exist. 

but chan and woojin's voices were always there to remind me to not listen, to "step out of them." and now whenever i'm low, at the voices return, i hear chan and woojin telling me to stay strong. i've never met skz and probably never will, but they comfort me better than anyone else in this world can even hope to, and for that i will love them forever.

text: So i have a story. In school i had 99% of the teachers and friends who would put me down every single day. Each day they would always have something to say especially the teachers. "I heard you were being rude u wont get anywhere no one will want you like this" "ur fat so its ok" "how can some people be so stupid as if u were never taught in school?" And many more of these irrelevant voices i keep hearing day and day for many years. I cried first alone then in my house then it got worse i cried in school open public she didnt bat a single eyelash i was thankful my friends were beside me but she really hurt me emotionally mentally physically. And for a fact she didnt even teach me anything. All the As i got were on my own effort no one else. Then my own relatives kept questioning me. I really was about to give up and one day my mind and my body couldnt take it no more so it shut down. I was out for 3 weeks. I woke up afterwards with no memory of anything but myself and my parents. I had nothing to relate to so i had to cope all alone. I made it this far.  Then i found this song. I found stray kids. I got emotional bc i truly understand. Finally. What i want to say is that if i can go through it so can you. We all can.

text: Maybe you'll never see my comment, but I'll talk anyway. I suffered a lot because of these voices and could not follow my thoughts, and I thanked them with tears of joy as I saw the words of the song. You have changed my life in a way that I do not even understand. Thank you. Thank you very much. My eyes fill with tears and tears when I listen to Voices, I finally found the right words to be said and heard. You made me have a reason to wake up and try to be happy. Once more, thank you. Chan Oppa, Hyun Jin, Chang Bin, Woo Jin Oppa, Jeong In, Felix, Min Ho Oppa, Seung Min and Ji Sung, I love you guys, and I am very excited about being there and being part of my life. Stay Fighting, we can do this.

author: @garretburrow
text:
Lemme tell you why these boys are rookie kings. In the ancient times of East Asia, when kings and queens would give birth to princes, the king would commission men of great renown to train and educate their son. Great philosophers and teachers would train their mind, & the greatest & most deadly martial artists would prepare their bodies for war; all in an effort to prepare them to one day inherit their father's kingdom(watch Marco Polo on Netflix to see what I mean.)
Nowadays, these princes don't go to war, but the comparison still applies. JYP is the king, & Stray Kids are his princes...or, to say it another way:
Rookie Kings.

author: @alyssabrelleayos6356
text: This video is not just aesthetically pleasing, visuals, talents or whatsoever you've seen but it also has a deep meaning. Changbin mentioned before that we'll love Voices since it has something that was similar to 'Hellevator' and it really is. Not just the MV that has similitarities but also the lyrics itself. People around them was against their dream and no one seemed to be in favor with them on whatever they do but inspite of that, they still do their best to persue their dreams no matter what. As you can see, they're wearing a mask. It's like it symbolizes that they're being suffocated by those people who keep on telling them to give up their dreams. As soon as they said "step out of them voices" they were being nagged by someone. Those people keep on repeating what they say to the point that their words are making them dizzy. In the end of the choreography, as you can see, their other hand was placed on their mouth and the other hand is at the back of their head and it's completely obvious that it's based on the lyrics "Break free from the voices in my head". It's like they can't say what they wanted to bcs there's a lot of people who keep on raising their voices towards them and it came to the point that they can't speak freely cuz they might judge them again. Im not really sure abt this HAHA imtiredtypingtho HAHAHA im not sure either if u get my point. i still have a lot to say but ermm. Sorry for my eng. Byeeee stream MY PACE.

author: @akiramin3870
text: When I was 7 my parents took me to a different country to live a better life since at the time we were extremely poor, but at least we were happy. The years passed by and I started feeling things that were hard for me to explain. By myself I had realized I had gotten depression and anxiety. I never told anyone because I never wanted to go to the doctor's. For me the doctors always left me so traumatized that I didn't even want to think about it. So I stayed quiet and just endured with the pain myself. I started feeling like a caged in bird and my mom never understood why I stay up in my room all day. I push myself away from everyone because I feel like the more I get to know them the more it will hurt me when they leave from the world. I'm now 24 years old and I've lived 17 years away from my relatives in my home country. At the beginning of this year we had decided we'd go back to our home country to start our own family business and to see our relatives again but...come July of this year my grandpa ends up passing away due to lung cancer. It was on its late stage and it ended up spreading everywhere in his body. I had come to realize that you can always find the time to explore. You can always make money. You can always make more friends no matter where you go. Money is not worth anything when it comes to love. There is so much time spent that you can never gain back. My mom always had me up to date with my grandpa so at least we got to see the funeral, but what hurts the most is that I've missed 17 years of him telling me wise and entertaining stories. I've missed so many ice creams we could have gotten together. I've missed all the family gatherings for the holidays and all the birthdays. Most importantly I've missed out on hugging him and kissing his cheek for 17 years. At school all the kids would always brag about going to their grandparents houses for the weekends for some special events. I always stayed quiet about those days. Just today my dad had called in to my job. He told my manager to let me go home earlier and to not tell me the reason why. They ended up closing anyways because a severe storm had formed. Once I arrived home my mom tells me that my other grandpa passed away. You could have had a really nice day but upon hearing news like this your world comes crashing in just mere seconds; however, the best part of my day is when I can run away from all the pain. When I can forget about everything and be reassured that everything will be alright. To me music is the best gateway out of hell and Stray Kids sure help out a lot. When I saw the recommendation to watch Hellevator I'm glad I clicked on the video. That was a year back or around there but when I had read the lyrics I was so impressed. I was moved and touched so I wondered who is this group? Why have I not heard of them yet? Why are they this good? They took all the frustration I'm feeling and managed to make it into a song! I didn't know about their show until Grrr came out since that's around the time I started watching it. Before I knew it I was already a fan. I listened to 3racha before I started watching the show since a friend had told me about them. The more information on them I kept receiving the more curious I kept getting. Each time I wanted to know more and more. To be honest at times I feel like I haven't even fully grasped all of it because the first thing I asked myself when I heard this song is, "They made this song??! They...Stray Kids.....3racha....Bang Chan a 22 year old Seo Changbin a 20 year old and Han Jisung a 19 year old(he has about a month but whatever)made a song like this?! I don't get it.....how is this possible???" These questions are what I ask myself because I keep feeling as if they've read my mind. I feel like we're so close when we're separated by oceans and land. I have my parents right by my side. I have Stray Kids in my heart telling me to escape from the voices in my head or I will go mad. This in itself is the best therapy I could ever ask for. So why would I need to go to the doctor's and waste more money when all they will do is prescribe drugs to me that I will not be able to take in the first place? Or recommend me to speak with a stranger as if the stranger is the one I need help with when I just need the love and support of those whom I love? Love is so powerful it can break everything and that's what I've always believed in. So I'll hold on to that hope till the very last chance I get. I will stay with Stray Kids for as long as I'm alive I will not leave their music out of my heart. Please continue to be yourselves no matter what changes may come and I promise I will stay just as I am. Once a Stay always a Stay and I will always be proud to say that. Sorry for my extremely long message but I hope some of you will pass through this comment and just appreciate what you have in life. I love you all no matter what you look like or what happens in your life. I hope you can all achieve your goals and wishes and if not all at least one. Be proud to be yourself and always love yourself. Always remember someone out there loves you and if you don't think so then you just haven't met them yet; you're also lying to yourself. Stay strong fam. ğŸ’ğŸ’•

author: @TheHottestinspirit
text:
This song really deserved it's own mv but I am already happy with this performance video. Voices is THE song for me, just like how Grow Up did it to me and Voices did the same thing to me. Such a deep, meaningful song that everyone can relate. Sometime we just wanted people to shut up, all those useless insults or comparison or mocking words to stop, and let us do whatever we want but because of those voices sometime it's get to us and we wanted it to stop what even scarier is those voices now became our own voice that kept putting down ourselves, kept thinking we're the worst, kept making our own selves weak, we hated it yet we did the same to ourself, not loving our own self having such a low confidence in our own self. We need to stop it.

 Let's break free from these voices! Thank you Stray Kids, even though all of you are younger than me but I actually learn more from these kids, they're the future of KPOP, I am sure this group will be bigger in the future, it's okay take all your time to be on top! "Don't compare yourself with others it's okay to run slower"

author: @lexiwilliams382
text:
This is my new favorite song!!! I appreciate Stray Kids so so much! I've been a Stay since pre-debut!!! They are extremely inspirational and motivated to let people hear what they have to say. They aren't afraid of the truth but rather face it and spread the word. I am overwhelmed with pride and love for these boys. I can't wait to continue watching them progress in their fame. They deserve the world. If you don't stan yet... You better stan them now.
.
.
On another note I'm so so proud and happy that Jeongin and Minho are finally getting the lines they deserve. Their voices are so beautiful. It's official that Changbin is the world's best rapper. If you don't agree, it's okay. Hyunjin has improved in so so many areas and I really could not be prouder. Jisung is so talented and beautiful... I literally have no words for him. He's absolutely amazing and impresses me more with everything he does. Seungmin and Woojin are still killing the notes and I'm so happy for them. Their voices are gorgeous and this album suits their voices very very well. Felix and his deep voice man... It still gets me... I mean, how in the world would we live had he not debuted with Stray Kids? He's so talented and beautiful and..... CHANGLIX. Y'all better not be sleeping on this ship.... Anyways... I'm so so so proud of Chan. He's such a great leader and I think the other members really do look up to him and he is doing so well. He can sing and rap, like boy, I want him to have some raps in the Stray Kids songs every once in a while. He deserves to be a rapper. His voice is still beautiful though!!! Overall though, I really appreciate his humor. It really keeps us all happy and positive. Welp that's it for this novel, until next time Stays.

text:
Korea and people in general should stop sleeping on stray kids. People would often look down on groups like stray kids and say their only gaining the popularity they have because theyâ€™re from a big company. Saying stuff like groups from a small company have to work much harder to be acknowledge whereas groups like stray kids gain immediate popularity. 

However, people doesnâ€™t realize that inside these big companies it is way more competitive. In order for stray kids to debut they have to constantly compete with other trainees. For example, cuz jyp is so big and competitive so many people would come and go because not everyone can debut. Bang chan withstand all of that for 7 years before he can finally debut as a jyp group. Stray kids work hard to get where they are. They deserve all and more success. 

Please donâ€™t be prejudiced against them or their popularity just because theyâ€™re from a big company. Have an open heart and listen to their music before deciding to blindly dislike them.

author: @mimitran7216
text:
They are behind masks because they have to hide their true voices and thoughts away from the toxic world full of judgement and hate but as time past, they slowly take off the masks, symbolizing that It is a time to speak out. They canâ€™t hide behind a mask no more. THEY have to be the voice who doesnâ€™t have one. Despite the hate in the world, the world needs to know how they feel and what theyâ€™re going through. This is truly such a beautiful song and mv.

Stray kids talks about falling down in life, teenage rebellion, losing yourself, being envious, school life and etc. They really are trying to shine a light to the public about what people are going through. They are giving a voice to people who does not have one.

I have much respect for them and I hope fans will continue to support them because they are certainly giving us support through their songs. They give life advice to make us into a better us. Hope they will become very successful one day.

author: @moli2419
text:
I Stan them since predebut, I saw them when they were 9,I saw them when they were 8,I saw them when they were 7 and I also saw them when we finally know they were going to debut with 9 kids,Kim WooJin,Bang Chan,Lee MinHo,Seo ChangBin,Hwang HyunJin,Han JiSung,Lee Felix,Kim SeungMin and Yang Jeong In;I was happy when they released a Mixtape and I watched all their MV's, I waited until they finally release "I Am Not",their album debut, I've been night without sleep watching to their music videos,climbing visits to District 9 and Mirror. I waited for them again, hearing to the same 14 song(+3Racha songs) every single day and night until now, that they released their second mini album "I Am Who". It's been a long time a know them,almost a year,and now I think I can say that I saw them grown up, not only in age but also like a group,they became better and better since I met them. Now, I am very proud of them,and very proud of see my 9 boys growing together,having fun together, smiling and crying together and I can't even be more proud of being a STAY,of being part of this huge family,which is growing and growing more with each passing day and I am happy to say that while I am conscious, I will never leave them, I will be at their side at every moment and I will see them reach the top and dreams. With no hesitate I'm gonna say it, I love you boys.

Stays always with Stray Kids.

author: @aiurihoon996
text: I actually didn't know each one of them before back when JYP boy group trainees were popping from here and there because seriously it was really hard to find informations about it but I was happy because finally a new group may come out any time soon then suddenly JYP releases Hellevator and I thought it was their debut and found out later it was for their survival program. I have been a fan since the first time I saw hellevator 30 minutes after it was released. Being with them since those pre-debut days really makes me emotional seeing the hardships they had to encounter to reach this goal of theirs to reach their dreams. The criticism they received during the survival show and almost not being able to debut. It's just so overwhelming seeing them where they are now out here not just giving us great songs but meaningful at the same time and things we all could relate too. They are out here showing us their stories and comforting each one of us with every problem we all have. STRAY KIDS IF YOU ARE READING THIS THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU SO MUCH FOR BRINGING BRIGHTNESS BACK INTO MY LIFE! Your songs are what keeps me going and I hope you get to reach more people out there through your songs and we STAYs will always be here for all of you no matter what. Depend on us like how we depend on you guys! We can be your light bearer just as you guys are ours. Stay healthy always and let's keep moving on our own pace together and shut the voices that brings us all down! ğŸ’•ğŸ’•ğŸ’• Stray Kids Fighting! ğŸ’•ğŸ’•ğŸ’•

So these last 2 years of high school are gonna be hell, was my first reaction. But then; Iâ€™ve changed, my teacherâ€™s changed. 13 year old me would have cried and cried for days. I only cried for 10 minutes and after this video realized that my hatred for her might just be a result of the state I was in when I met her. So basically theyâ€™re just voices telling me to hate her. Thatâ€™s how this song helped me just now. So if I stay optimistic, I might survive this.

So, for the 5th time in my life, Iâ€™m gonna pack my books and hope for the best.

author: @tarakana8805
text: *Being a predebut fan, this is really hard to watch all the way without crying. Hellevator was the first the world had seen of them. That was only October 6th of last year. They've come such a long way in less than a year. Each and every one of them have gone through something in their life that everyone can relate to in some way, which they talk about in a lot of their music. Even at such a young age, they're accomplishing so much. They're talking about topics that nobody has before. They aren't your normal rookie group, either. They've been so close ever since their trainee days, which you don't normally see. Thank you, Stray Kids, for being such an inspiration to me and other STAYs. I believe you all will continue to accomplish many things in the future. We will STAY by your side, all the way. But take all the time you need. It's okay to go slow. Until then, don't compare yourselves.*

text: *At first I was this is sure a fanmade because it's too good to be true, and then I was screaming. This song really deserved it's own mv but I am already happy with this performance video. Voices is THE song for me, just like how Grow Up did it to me and Voices did the same thing to me. Such a deep, meaningful song that everyone can relate. Sometime we just wanted people to shut up, all those useless insults or comparison or mocking words to stop, and let us do whatever we want but because of those voices sometime it's get to us and we wanted it to stop even scarier is those voices are actually our own voice that kept putting down ourselves, kept thinking we're the worst, kept making our ownselves weak, we hated it yet we did the same to ourself, not loving our ownself having such a low confidence in our ownself. We need to stop it. Thank you Stray Kids, even though all of you are younger than me but I actually learn more from these kids, they're the future of KPOP, I am sure this group will be bigger in the future, it's okay take all your time to be on top! "Don't compare yourself with others it's okay to run slower"*

author: @loxee4769
text:
This song makes me cry. I've been dealing with mental issues my whole life long, but only a few years ago have I developed an eating disorder, which fills my head with voices like no disease has ever done before. This song radiates a feeling I know all too well. This song portrays my feelings of being suffocated and anxious perfectly, it makes me feel understood.
Thank you guys so much for this song. There's so much happening in my life right now and I am genuinely thankful for a song so comforting and helpful to your fans. Thank you so much.
